{"commentv2": 1, "number": 0, "id": 372515, "nreplies": 13, "sticky": 0, "user": "Dimanoid", "body": "No idea why last boss is called \"Kronus\" here, actually his name in \"Loken\".\r\nDoing moderate melee damage, from time to time casting AOE lighting which can be easy avoided - just run away (include tank). Had no problems with him, killed from the first try.", "date": "2008-09-09T12:50:31-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Important to Note:  Keyboard turning = fail  Backing up to get away = fail  Turning with mouse or strafing = win", "creationdate": "2008-12-29T15:56:06-06:00", "id": 68600, "rating": 127, "commentid": 372515, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "176454", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "The DOT that jumps to other party members is pretty irrelevant.  We ignored that aspect of the fight and did not have problems healing through it.  Tank and healer need to stay on top of their game, don't give up if a DPS or two die, you could theoretically do this fight with just two people as Loken's damage output when you dodge his AOE and stay close to him otherwise is rather low.", "creationdate": "2009-01-02T05:32:02-06:00", "id": 69521, "rating": 11, "commentid": 372515, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "shadyadvocate", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "he looks very very bored", "creationdate": "2009-01-25T01:47:53-06:00", "id": 75276, "rating": 94, "commentid": 372515, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "250546", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "For anyone having trouble running away from Lightning Nova, move the camera 180 degrees before he casts. When he starts casting the Nova, simply use the mouse to run away.", "creationdate": "2009-02-17T23:34:37-06:00", "id": 80808, "rating": 2, "commentid": 372515, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "201364", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Just tried a new strat yesterday.  Instead of running from the circle to the stairs, tank him in front of the two posts/columns that are on the left and right of the room.  I tanked him like that yesterday and it was absurdly easy, even with 2 melee dps.  If your heals can't keep you all up through the nova, try this.  I find it much easier then the stairs run, which I had done every time before.", "creationdate": "2009-02-27T09:18:53-06:00", "id": 82741, "rating": 3, "commentid": 372515, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "greyjasper", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-09-09T12:51:10-05:00", 1, "Dimanoid"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 1, "id": 373430, "nreplies": 21, "sticky": 0, "user": "92105", "body": "Used to be called Kronus but Blizzard changed it.\r\n\r\nThere's a \"Thorim\" in Storm Peaks who is Loken's..brother, I think? Something like that, at anyrate. Thorim is the \"good\" one and Loken the \"bad\" one.\r\n\r\nGiven the massive grab from Norse mythology throughout Northrend, it's clearly a stab at Thor and Loki.", "date": "2008-09-10T21:25:31-05:00", "rating": 96, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Hehe, norse mythology pays off...  Loke (or Loki) was the so-called evil Aesthir (norse pantheon of gods), and he betrayed the other gods and even sired a demon known as Udg\u00e5rdsloke/Utgaardsloki.  Thor was another Aesthir, son of Odin (who was the all-seeing father of them), and Thor also had a boomeranging hammer, Mjolnir.[s] He supposedly defeats Loke in Ragnarok, the norse version of Armageddon and judgement day.[/s]  So, besides Thorium being radioactive and existing IRL, Blizzard has obviously gotten some \"inspiration\" for Northrend from ancient Viking myths...  Oh, and it should be said", "creationdate": "2008-09-10T21:25:32-05:00", "id": 350388, "rating": 76, "commentid": 373430, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "paddymew", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I dont know where you where tought nothern mythology but it aint the same way we learn it in Denmark thats for sure :)  Now this is not just for ranting but for educational purposes :P  1. Utgaardsloke is not Loki's son, or related to him at all. Nor is he a Deamon, but a giant. (Loki btw is halfgiant).  2. As mentioned Thor doesn't kill Loki. What he does though is lead the Aesthir in their hunt for Loki after they realise that Loki was responcible for the death of Thors brother Balder. They tie him up with a combination of large round rocks and the intestines of one of his sons (which they o", "creationdate": "2008-09-10T21:25:32-05:00", "id": 362442, "rating": 39, "commentid": 373430, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Weareallangels", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Actually, Thor wasn't supposed to kill Loki in Ragnarok, he was supposed to kill Jormungand, the World Serpent, (http://www.wowwiki.com/Jormungar), and Loki was to be killed by Heimdall, the gatekeeper of Asgard, the home of the Norse gods", "creationdate": "2008-09-27T22:45:10-05:00", "id": 48302, "rating": 49, "commentid": 373430, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "221073", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Which inspired the Jormungar worms.  Also, Utgard Keep (And pinnacle) are located in Howling Fjord - Not Borean Tundra.", "creationdate": "2008-10-30T12:45:43-05:00", "id": 53547, "rating": 40, "commentid": 373430, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "106166", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "You never know, there might be a nine-legged horse mount introduced as a drop from this encounter at some point.   (If you don't know what i am talking about, don't frigging downrate me.)", "creationdate": "2009-02-12T07:19:34-06:00", "id": 79598, "rating": 71, "commentid": 373430, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Volcan", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 2, "id": 374495, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Ceryx", "body": "He'll give the entire party a debuff that does damage based on how far away from the boss they are (and will put everyone in combat by doing so, will remove stealth as well.) Damage from this can be minimized by having the entire party stack close, and having everyone run out from the AOE to the same spot.", "date": "2008-09-12T10:21:31-05:00", "rating": 18, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 3, "id": 379272, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "214152", "body": "Really easy boss, unforgiving when you don't know what to do tho. Basically the same as Murmur on Heroic mode. Stack on boss when dpsing, and run away when he's casting his aoe. This is for regular mode. Also take note not to run too far away. The further you run, the more aoe damage you take from his aura. Hits rather hard too.", "date": "2008-09-17T21:09:10-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Me (80 frost tank DK) and a priest (79 holy/disc) ended basically 2-manning him, the others in our group died when he was around 80%. Took a long time but eventually we killed him, lol.", "creationdate": "2008-11-25T15:31:18-06:00", "id": 363974, "rating": 1, "commentid": 379272, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Fatality", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-09-17T21:10:28-05:00", 1, "214152"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 4, "id": 405282, "nreplies": 4, "sticky": 0, "user": "ArgentSun", "body": "A relatively easy way to do this fight is to have the group DPS him on the circle he starts at, and run back the line towards the circular area where the two giants were roaming. After his Lightning Nova is finished, just go back to the circle, rinse and repeat.", "date": "2008-10-13T23:38:52-05:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Drag him to the little circle on his platform at the start of the fight. Face him to right or left and start fighting with all group on top of him. Facing him to either side means, all party can move faster when you need to run out of nova by strifing ;)  When he starts casting his AOE nova, run to the bottom of stairs that leads to his platform. It is enough to outrange his nova.  Do NOT run back to circle after the nova. Instead stay where you are and fight him at the bottom of stairs. Run to circle on next nova. Keep alternating between this two tanking spots through the fight.  This way yo", "creationdate": "2008-10-13T23:38:53-05:00", "id": 354633, "rating": 70, "commentid": 405282, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "29778", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Great strat by Anakha.  With an emphasis on \"staying where you are\" after u run to avoid his nova.  This is crucial for FERAL DRUID & PROT WARRIORS.  As soon as you run out of the nova, DO NOT make the mistake of charging at him.  Unless your party got to within melee range before you did, you should not do this.  The distance that u create between you & your party will subject them to his range dps which makes this fight a lot harder.  Instead, have your party group around you & wait for him to come.  He doesn't reset aggro after the nova so if you've put enough threat on him, this shouldn't ", "creationdate": "2008-10-13T23:38:53-05:00", "id": 368967, "rating": 6, "commentid": 405282, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "68102_", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Just tried this on my first HoL run, and it worked beautifully.", "creationdate": "2008-12-17T21:12:20-06:00", "id": 372110, "rating": 4, "commentid": 405282, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "266356", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "The thing about this strat, is it will increase caster dps [u]slightly[/u].  And that is all.  We're talking one cast.  Meanwhile the melee is doing no damage, and I've found my groups to be leaning more towards the melee side since WotLK hit and everyone rolled a DK and all the warriors went fury.  Still a viable strategy but claiming that it will increase your dps much is really not true.", "creationdate": "2009-02-03T16:57:04-06:00", "id": 385767, "rating": 3, "commentid": 405282, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "51169", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 5, "id": 435612, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "86526", "body": "Moving together as a group when out-ranging his nova is definately a viable strat, but one ability Loken has that makes the fight harder than you might realize is a lightning dot he casts on a seemingly random player that jumps to another nearby player after it ends and starts again increasing its damage each time.  The damage eventually caps but especially on heroic mode this ability will continue to do a [b]lot[/b] of damage unless the player with the dot moves away from the rest of the group. (and takes more damage himself from the range-based aura)  Loken will cast a new dot soon after, but its damage will be reset to the initial minimal ticks.", "date": "2008-11-08T18:01:21-06:00", "rating": 15, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 6, "id": 450297, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "83565", "body": "Lightning nova can NOT be LOS'd.", "date": "2008-11-17T11:01:42-06:00", "rating": 37, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Confirmed, with great results!  There is no great need to run away to reset the debuff from the dot, a group on heroic in a mix of level 70, levelling quest and very few 80 heroic drops managed it once everyone could alternate two spots effectively, although i'm in no doubt that CoH was very handy. DPS wasnt even massively high and we still got some achievement for killing him in under 2 minutes, although personally if it lasted longer than that then we probably wouldn't have made it.  Still, it was nice to have a little bit of a challenge to break us up from facerolling easy bosses. (even if ", "creationdate": "2008-11-17T11:01:43-06:00", "id": 361967, "rating": 10, "commentid": 450297, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "prolo", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "It can be LoS, not sure if its a bug or not. DPS and Healer failed to understand the concept of \"Stack on Tank\" and promtly died. Alot. I'm messing around after they all died, keeping myself alive for as long as possible (about 30 seconds). He started casting Lightning Nova and I ran to the other side of a pillar right next to him and it didn't do any damage. It worked twice out of about 4 or 5 Nova's.", "creationdate": "2009-01-07T07:16:02-06:00", "id": 378357, "rating": 0, "commentid": 450297, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "GinjaNinja", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "As far away you have ran then less damage you will take by the Nova as he said it can not be missed,but take less damage:Yes", "creationdate": "2009-08-08T13:25:34-05:00", "id": 419324, "rating": 0, "commentid": 450297, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "301983", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 7, "id": 450485, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "247691", "body": "Did the boss in heroic mode today, the AOE lightning does around 14k, and his debuff does around 1.5k at 10y distance. Just stay under the boss and move away when he cast the AOE, everyone needs a lot of healing, so a Druid or Priest is much prefered.", "date": "2008-11-17T12:14:58-06:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 8, "id": 457888, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "HolgerDK", "body": "Seems like he only casts Arc Lighting after Lightning Nova.", "date": "2008-11-20T06:28:03-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 9, "id": 458848, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Nokturnal", "body": "HEROIC MODE\n\nThe trick to the fight is basically the Eagle Boss from ZA in reverse.\n\nStay collapsed on top of him entire fight until he casts Lightning Cloud, then run away from him. \n\nDO NOT run as a group from Lightning Cloud as previously mentioned in comments, stay spread out.\n\nLightning arc is a dot he randomly casts during fight that targets one player, after it ticks on you it will try to jump to someone else, if you are spread out it can't jump anywhere. The dot gains dmg with each jump so staying spread out during Lightning Cloud is a good idea.", "date": "2008-11-20T14:52:58-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-11-20T14:53:26-06:00", 2, "Nokturnal"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 10, "id": 459016, "nreplies": 6, "sticky": 0, "user": "amphitrite", "body": "No...do stay together on heroic.\r\n\r\n3 things that make this fight one of the easiest fights in the game on heroic.\r\n1. His aoe tick is based on you near him and near your group. It hits harder the farther you are apart.\r\n2. His big aoe will one shot you\r\n3. after his big aoe, he will run right at the tank\r\n\r\nIf you stay on the white line..make it so easy.\r\n\r\nGroup on your tank in the center circle and smack him down until his aoe. Run down the white line until his aoe goes off...like 1 second, and go again. When he aoes, run down the white line again. You'll get 3-4 aoes down the white line. Once he does it again, go back up the white line towards the circle. Back and forth...\r\n\r\nYour party will take up for 5k ticks from his normal aoe if you spread out. If you stay together when you run, hell come right to your tank and you'll only take one big tick.\r\n\r\nWe wiped 3 times trying it every other way. Once we did this we easily one shot him, and I was more then 1/2 mana still.", "date": "2008-11-20T16:04:11-06:00", "rating": 55, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "This is our strat as well. We walk him down the white line starting from the circle till we outrange the AOE, about 15 yards, spank him at the end of the floor, then keep moving him down the stairs, repeating till he dies. Got the 2 minute kill achievement with this strategy. There's no healer outside of twentyfifthnovember that can heal through the aoe in Heroic mode.", "creationdate": "2008-11-21T14:40:56-06:00", "id": 362792, "rating": 4, "commentid": 459016, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "franzie", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Yeah just tried this on heroic. Stacking up on the boss reduces the damage you take from his aura so is a must and walking down the line makes it really easy to stick 2gether when he does his aoe.  Unfortunately even when we did it perfect our healer ran oom before we got him down using shadowfiend, innervate and a pot.   Just a gear check boss once you follow the 'stick to the line' strat.", "creationdate": "2008-11-23T23:52:36-06:00", "id": 58797, "rating": 5, "commentid": 459016, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Fatherfury", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I healed through the Aoe, and I'm in heroic and 80 blues.  Antimagic zone and NR totem helped though.", "creationdate": "2008-11-30T22:42:53-06:00", "id": 365661, "rating": 1, "commentid": 459016, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Garroa", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Did this on my JUST dinged 80 disc priest on heroic, shielded everyone before nova, popped Inner Focus and Divine Hymn and everyone was at full health. DPS was decent enough he didn't do another.", "creationdate": "2009-08-13T01:14:51-05:00", "id": 115761, "rating": 1, "commentid": 459016, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "315080", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I can't emphasize it enough - STAY ON TOP OF THE TANK.  Today on heroic we wiped 3 times, I was healing (priest). Spammed PoH and everything else but it just won't work if your group is clueless... Ended up being insulted and kicked from the group - not cool.", "creationdate": "2010-01-29T18:24:50-06:00", "id": 145954, "rating": 1, "commentid": 459016, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "15173", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 11, "id": 459766, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Shooya", "body": "His epic drops are:\r\n\r\n[url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=37855]Mail Girdle of the Audient Earth[/url]\r\n[url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=37852]Colossal Skull-Clad Cleaver[/url]\r\n[url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=37853]Advanced Tooled-Leather Bands[/url]\r\n[url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=37854]Woven Bracae Leggings[/url]", "date": "2008-11-20T22:17:21-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 12, "id": 460542, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "SamLocke07", "body": "Not sure if anyone has tried this yet but I recently watched the Project Lore: Boss Kill, Loken. (http://www.wowhead.com/?projectlore=wotlk-2.9) and they LoS (line of sighted) the AoE and took no damage what so ever.\r\n\r\nAll they did was group up on the boss, causing only 400-500 dmg per aura tick and then on the AoE they all went behind 1 of 4 pillars around Loken, causing no damage to any of them.\r\n\r\nCan someone test this and let me know? Thanks.", "date": "2008-11-21T07:05:35-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "You can not use LOS to avoid the AOE. We just tried it on Heroic Mode.", "creationdate": "2008-11-21T19:44:00-06:00", "id": 58194, "rating": 10, "commentid": 460542, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "114397", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "They did not LoS the nova. They simply ran out of range (20 yards) and happened to also be behind a pillar. Running at least 20 yards away within the 5 second cast time is the only way to avoid it.", "creationdate": "2009-07-18T23:54:42-05:00", "id": 110540, "rating": 0, "commentid": 460542, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "mjblink", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 13, "id": 461775, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "lazareth", "body": "We found that we were able to interrupt his AoE if we kicked it at the last couple seconds of his cast.  Not sure if this is a bug or intended.", "date": "2008-11-21T21:11:54-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Didn't work for us, tried both kicking, counterspelling and shieldbashing.", "creationdate": "2008-11-21T22:48:10-06:00", "id": 58235, "rating": 14, "commentid": 461775, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "bebbe", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Once everyone goes out of range of the Nova he'll stop casting it and run towards the tank. It isn't being interrupted it's just a fight mechanic.", "creationdate": "2008-11-23T05:11:43-06:00", "id": 363247, "rating": 5, "commentid": 461775, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Psychowolf", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 14, "id": 463965, "nreplies": 7, "sticky": 0, "user": "130654", "body": "Well, in heroic mode we attempted many times to alternate 2 spots where to tank him, but usually someone died very fast once he moved a bit more away from Loken. \r\n\r\nWe decided to try and soak the lightning nova,and just stand still all the time, so his aura does minimal harm. We all had healthstones, blessing of sanctuary, devotion aura to help healing and nature resist totem, and everyone party was over 13k hp...stam food or such can help there. \r\n\r\nThis way you have minimal damage going on cept the nova. While the nova has 4s cast time, you can make sure everyone is topped off before it hits, and a shammy could heal it up really fast so we were safe for next nova.\r\n\r\nThanks to this causing all the party damage being completely predictable, as long as your healer can keep up and your party wont get oneshot (not many people have less than 14k hp lately), it makes the fight really easy, also, judgement of light and such things help a lot here.\r\n\r\nEDIT: ok,today we had a holy pally there, no healthstones or pots, and the group insisted on moving from the nova...after 4 wipes they decided to give my stupid idea a try, and gotta say that even with holy pally, who lacks any sort of AoE heals, the fight is extremely easy when everyone just stands on top of tank.", "date": "2008-11-22T19:34:48-06:00", "rating": 29, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I agree. We just finished this boss on Heroic and the moving back and forth just wasn't working.  Your best bet, if you have any sort of decent gear (we were in T6/Sunwell/Wrath Blues) is just stand close to him and burn everything you can to nuke him down and keep yourself alive. You basically have about 3 novas before people will start dropping.  From a Warlock PoV, Nether Protection owns this fight. 5k novas are laughable when you have ~20k health.  If you can handle it, this is an easy way to get the achievement to kill him in under 2mins.", "creationdate": "2008-11-23T04:01:19-06:00", "id": 58620, "rating": 20, "commentid": 463965, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "GenericNPC", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "just saying, this boss is rediculously easy with nature resist totem and healing stream totem, i have no trouble at all healing it now. mana isnt normally an issue since the boss is normally killed under 3 minutes", "creationdate": "2008-12-07T02:29:11-06:00", "id": 62618, "rating": 6, "commentid": 463965, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "jackpfree", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I want to give another +1 to this strat.  My group yesterday (prot pally, shaman healer, mage, lock and hunter) wiped 4 times using the stacked run method on heroic even with the nature resist totem.  So we tried just absorbing the damage....  The result was phenomenal!  We not only beat Loken by sitting together and not moving, but we got the achievement.  I highly recommend using this strategy if you have a shaman and/or other highly efficient AoE healer.", "creationdate": "2009-01-02T09:55:38-06:00", "id": 69567, "rating": 4, "commentid": 463965, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "295186", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "i agree about this being the best tactics when working with healadins or resto shammys, we tried this with priest partially T7 geared we wiped and wiped and wiped andwiped..., same for the running tactic, even if 1 dps soaked up the nova he died (me for instance as a fury wairor with over 23k hp died 10 secs later from the ticks of his aura) we did most dmg getting blasted by the nova and healing up, GL :)", "creationdate": "2009-01-04T07:16:00-06:00", "id": 70101, "rating": 0, "commentid": 463965, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "khoros", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This strategy is extremely easy for disc priest. Mana is almost no problem thanks to all the DA shields that pop up after aoe heals. Just keep shield on cooldown by using it on anyone with lowest hp that doesn't yet have weakened soul debuff, precast prayer of healing when he casts his aoe and keep prayer of mending on cooldown. When 2-3 players need healing just use flash heal, prayer of healing or (glyphed) holy nova otherwise.", "creationdate": "2009-03-30T08:35:24-05:00", "id": 88424, "rating": 2, "commentid": 463965, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "205529", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-12-07T19:19:30-06:00", 2, "130654"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 15, "id": 465804, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Fugazi", "body": "This boss can be easy or big pain in the ass.\n\nWhat you need to know:\n- You want to stay close to him.\n- You do not want to stay close to someone else.\n- You do not want to be hit by aoe.\n\nSo simply you need to be close to boss keeping distance of each other (tank especially) and when he cast aoe you run away 20+ yards and then come back as soon as possible.\n\n- If you got hit by Lightning Nova - you ran too slow or/and not far enough.\n- If you got hit by Arc Lightning by someone (not boss) or you hit someone with it - you were too close to each other.\nKeep avoiding above and try to stay as close to boss and possible and it will be easy.\n\nEDIT: Above is for heroic.", "date": "2008-11-23T18:21:00-06:00", "rating": 20, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Agreed the \"standing on top of him and soaking the damage\" strat is more effective for just about all groups. I've run this place three times and each time the group tried the running strat first, never got it to work, and the second and third runs were successful with the standing strat.  Also this boss has to be a contender for having longest, most annoying run back after a wipe.", "creationdate": "2009-01-18T16:34:53-06:00", "id": 381537, "rating": 0, "commentid": 465804, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Robyn", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-11-23T20:02:34-06:00", 1, "Fugazi"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 16, "id": 465891, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "ThyFlame", "body": "Just use the big white line on the ground, the throne and the orb as your reference points.\r\n\r\nStart at the throne.  After the first nova, run south to the orb (roughly to the stairs).  Everyone stops and waits and healer does his thing.  \r\n\r\nTank WAITS for the boss to COME TO HIM.  If you charge back in, everyone is now separated, loses DPS time and more importantly gets you behind on healing.\r\n\r\nSecond nova run back to the throne.\r\n\r\nRinse and repeat.\r\n\r\n\r\nDon't pug this and don't bring healers with lag or slow reaction times.  They will fail (first hand experience).", "date": "2008-11-23T20:02:15-06:00", "rating": 6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 17, "id": 466608, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "255048", "body": "We had some serious problems with this boss due to coordination and running out in time. I decided to just stand in and soak the AoE(14k unresisted damage) but had the shaman drop nature resist totem(it IS nature) and dropped it to 8-9k, a very manageable AoE.\r\nHope that helps.\r\nOur group setup was also a feral tank/balance druid/arms warrior/frost mage/restoration shaman", "date": "2008-11-24T06:47:18-06:00", "rating": 13, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 18, "id": 467699, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Kickkiller", "body": "my grp was\r\n\r\nme (resto shaman)\r\nDK unholy\r\nHunter\r\nMage\r\nWarrior tank\r\n\r\n\r\nWhat we did was we kited him futher away from his throne each time.\r\n\r\nI have a good sence of time, and i counted chain heals between AoE thing, and it was 6 CHs, which is around 20 seconds..\r\n\r\nso every time i made 5 CHs i moved away and charged my new CH to prepare etc.\r\n\r\nWe did it easyly when we got control of it..\r\n\r\nAlso, a good thing is to move before he starts casting, so you dont have to either cancel a spell, or wait for it to go off!", "date": "2008-11-24T17:55:19-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 19, "id": 468395, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Mazuli", "body": "My group consisted of 4 melee and me, a resto shaman.  Basically we tanked him at the throne until the nova.  When he did the nova we ran south down the white line.  He died after 3 novas.  We made sure all melee stood in front of him next to the tank so they could get away from the nova in time as well, even if it meant parried attacks.  After that we ran back to him and repositioned ourselves.  Rinse and repeat.  As the healer all I did was lesser healing wave.  Chain heal takes too long to cast and the fight is so short (and I'm taking damage that eats water shields) that mana efficiency isn't a problem.  Very easy fight if everyone can be coordinated.  Later on it'll be easy when people are geared and make stupid mistakes but for now only take competent people.", "date": "2008-11-25T01:43:08-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 20, "id": 468514, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Martyr017", "body": "If your having troubles on this boss, I have made a video to help you with it.\r\n\r\nhttp://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1H3Z5ZGQEuY\r\n\r\nBest luck to you.", "date": "2008-11-25T03:05:40-06:00", "rating": 20, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 21, "id": 470602, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Spinnacer", "body": "Probably the hardest 5-man HC boss. It's barely PUGable. It sounds easy enough but he also casts http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=52921#used-by-npc a dot that damages all nearby groupmebers, ticks every sec, add to that his aura. There goes 8k hp for everyone, meanwhile the tank is getting meleed hard.\n\nOh someone didn't quite make it out the nova.. etc..\n\nIf you're going in PUG, Bring 2 healers, seriously. (Note. Holy Paladins can't handle all the AoE damage. Get someone with proper AoE-heals.", "date": "2008-11-25T23:08:16-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "It's true. Take a look at this: http://forums.worldofwarcraft.com/thread.html?topicId=13275298122&sid=1&pageNo=10#182. Ghostcrawler confirms it as the hardest heroic boss in WotLK. He is the reason why he made it to the #1 spot in \"Most Dangerous Creatures\" list now, just like Vaelastrasz the Corrupt did back in vanilla WoW.", "creationdate": "2008-12-05T20:05:34-06:00", "id": 62240, "rating": 3, "commentid": 470602, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "catspats31", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I solo healed it as a Holy Paladin yesterday. Granted, it wasn't easy and we had a couple of wipes as we fine tuned our strategy, but it is indeed possible. Don't give up!", "creationdate": "2008-12-27T02:34:40-06:00", "id": 67953, "rating": 2, "commentid": 470602, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Discolando", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-11-25T23:12:45-06:00", 4, "Spinnacer"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 22, "id": 472614, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "151381", "body": "Listed as WoW's Most Dangerous Mob on the official site for Nov 25th 2008, with over[b] 88,000 [/b]people wiping on him!", "date": "2008-11-26T21:19:29-06:00", "rating": 46, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "If anyone is wondering where this is listed: http://www.worldofwarcraft.com/toplist/ In the last 6 days starting 12/17/08, he was #3,#1,#1,#1,#1, and #2 respectively.", "creationdate": "2008-12-25T19:43:28-06:00", "id": 67676, "rating": 5, "commentid": 472614, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "167540", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 23, "id": 473020, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "254912", "body": "We killed him yesterday on heroic mode.\r\n1 warrior (me) tanking, shaman healer, deathknight, rogue and druid dpsing.\r\nIn order to avoid positioning him properly between novas we had preset a route I'd take towards the entrance of the room and everyone followed that direction everytime he started casting nova.\r\nSo no running back and forth needed and the whole group was automatically standing in front of him in order to minimize the distance people had to run.\r\nNova is 20yards radius so you can check when to stop running by looking at your taunt button.", "date": "2008-11-27T02:53:37-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Well I have never posted on wowhead until now.  I know many people might have found this strategy already but for all you pally healers and groups with a pally healer that might be having issues with this boss.  Aoe damage sucks for holy pallys, moving sucks for holy pallys, aoe moving really sucks for holy pallys.    Which is what this fight is suppose to be, so lets simplify it.  Start the fight like normal have your whole group close to the boss to avoid aoe damage when the nova is coming,[u] just sit there soak it up[/u].  By the time your doing this place on heroic \"most\" players should h", "creationdate": "2008-11-27T02:53:38-06:00", "id": 373998, "rating": 0, "commentid": 473020, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "287481", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Need to post that its better 4 maning him....easyer to heal....(Not actually 4 maning..i just died at a 300k hp :p) Really....My group 4 maned him....", "creationdate": "2008-12-19T12:36:01-06:00", "id": 372628, "rating": 0, "commentid": 473020, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "stathisdjs", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This was correct when posted, but remember that Taunt is 30 yards now.", "creationdate": "2009-01-26T11:32:41-06:00", "id": 383681, "rating": 0, "commentid": 473020, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "280222", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 24, "id": 474291, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "derxer89", "body": "I can only warn you from trying this guy with pugs.\r\nit needs only one lowbob that screws up when the nova comes and you wont likely be able to dps him down fast enough.", "date": "2008-11-27T16:32:05-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 25, "id": 474427, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "ksjoet", "body": "After dowing this boss a couple of times and wiping the best strategy is to designate a running path to everyone when they run from nova. You need to do this to get rid of the arc lightning debuffs. So have one party member run south, one west, one north and one east. The tank can be standing to soak it up if you got a good group or he can run. If the tank is running I suggest he runs in almost the same direction as the healer. This is to minimize the running distance for the healer so he can as much as possible stand still and heal. \r\n\r\nSo hug him, spread out when nova comes, run back in and pew pew. Even if 2 DPS dies you can still get him down if the rest of you do it correctly. Also if someone is lagging or have bad MS it's almost impossible to run away from the nova. I had 600ms the other day and even if I were standing at 5-10yd from the boss I still never managed to run out even if I was way clear of it on my own screen.", "date": "2008-11-27T18:07:57-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 26, "id": 476124, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "100447", "body": "just killed by 3men group (HC). Warr tank, restosham, lock.\r\nCombat duration 3.23min, but longer fight is better for healer then heal 5man group damaged by aura dmg.......\r\nYou should try it :)", "date": "2008-11-28T14:49:11-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 27, "id": 476450, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Nishika", "body": "Easy boss. Stay together, nuke him down, run away when he does AoE. Drag him down the white line on the floor, then it's easy for people to stay together. If you run out of space, any decent tank knows how to force the boss to step backwards :-)\r\n\r\nThis is how we do it:\r\nhttp://www.wegame.com/watch/Loken_in_Halls_of_Lightning_Heroic/", "date": "2008-11-28T17:51:36-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 28, "id": 479582, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "wutz", "body": "My guildmates have killed him in heroic recently with achievement (kill him in less than 2 min). After several wipes they decided no to avoid AoE and just stayed in boss all the time. His aoe hits for 10-15k, so if the whole group has more than 15k hp, you can try this tactics. Seems to be very easy with resto shaman or holy priest.", "date": "2008-11-30T04:00:03-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-07-31T06:13:17-05:00", 1, "wutz"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 29, "id": 480194, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Dimanoid", "body": "If you have good DPS (no matter ranged or melee) and any type of AoE healer you can kill him just by zerging. All stand together and nuke. Dont run away even on nova, it strikes hard but you can survive with good equip. Resto shaman is the best choice, heroism+chainheal. Killed him 2 times this way on HC.", "date": "2008-11-30T11:15:36-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 30, "id": 485623, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "azanul", "body": "My group spent 2 days trying to clear this guy on heroic, we tried every strat...\r\nWe tried healing through the aoe, kiting down the white line, running through him at start of the cast.\r\nWe tried a constant kite strategy, nothing worked. \r\n\r\nHow we finally cleared it:\r\nHave your tank, pull him and stand in the circle in front of his throne. Stand at max melee range from Loken... mark your tank with a raid symbol, and have everyone stand [b]ontop of your tank (at max melee range)[/b]. This will cause a bit more damage from the dot due to being further away from Loken but it makes running a lot easier.\r\n\r\n(A helpful hint, pan your view around so your screen is facing in the direction you're going to be running to. Wait for the system message \"Loken begins to cast\" and just click both mouse buttons forcing your character to run in the direction of your view...)\r\n\r\nRun down the line about 10 yards, have your tank turn Loken around so you're facing his throne...stay at max melee range again. Next cast run to the circle where you first pull him. Rinse and repeat. We cleared him first attempt and got the 2 minute achievement trying it this way.", "date": "2008-12-02T18:00:35-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "10 yds won't do it. It's a 20 yd range AoE.", "creationdate": "2008-12-04T21:58:22-06:00", "id": 61995, "rating": 1, "commentid": 485623, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "jaxsonbateman", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 31, "id": 485665, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Lightrain", "body": "Ok, from a holy pally PoV, who actually doesn't have much gear, but enough for heroics.....\r\n\r\nDid this on heroic, and was actually quite easy as long as everyone gets out of the AoE cast.  That is the deal breaker.\r\n\r\nMy plan as a pally, since I have [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=53563]Beacon of Light[/url], is stack stack stack.  This makes this fight very easy, and very managable.  Since I, the healer, can not move once I'm casting, everyone stacks on me after nova.  The fight starts, stack on tank, if he takes damage, an instant holy shock(BTW, as a pally, starting a fight is the most crucial.  Seal of * that you use for healing, Beacon of light on tank as well as [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=53601]Sacred shield[/url].  Everyone stacks, and this makes the Jumping attack a benefit.  When it jumps, heal the party member that takes damage.  This heals the tank as well.  Beacon of light makes this fight easy as long as everyone is quick enough to get out of the aoe.  You move as a group.  After the aoe, the tank gets the boss to stop a few yards away, backs up to the party, and the fight resumes.  The \"bounce\" damage actually makes it so the gradual damage from his aura gets healed as well eventually.  This makes coordination easy.  I don't see why a small heal or HoT can't handle the same function, and do this the same way with the other healing classes.  Start at the top, and travel down toward the bottom of the stairs.  \r\n\r\nStacking on the tank seems to reduce his damage intake.  Is this part of the fight?", "date": "2008-12-02T18:21:19-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-12-02T18:28:34-06:00", 1, "Lightrain"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 32, "id": 488944, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "219351", "body": "Man this boss took me 8 deaths,5 hours and 2 groups to finally kill. Your whole group needs to be on the ball because one stuff up will meen a wipe. Finally downed him when everyone miraculously followed me to next tanking spot, didn't get hit by lightning nova(alot) and used cool downs at the right time.\n\nEdit:This boss is topping the wow top list:\nhttp://www.worldofwarcraft.com/toplist/", "date": "2008-12-04T06:06:06-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-12-05T17:53:46-06:00", 1, "219351"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 33, "id": 492669, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "183171", "body": "Our best attempts on heroic involved the tank not moving and eating the nova.  Party members spread around the boss in a circle, maintaining enough distance to avoid spreading the lightning debuff but also being close enough to minimize the aoe tick damage.  When he cast his lightning nova, all members except the tank merely moved backwards five or six yards to avoid the nova then moved right back in.  No kiting involved.  This avoided the nova spike damage and the quickness of the movement meant that the healer was less troubled by not being able to heal due to running.  Unfortunately, we were simply under geared for the encounter and lost some people right before repops.", "date": "2008-12-05T23:41:43-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 34, "id": 493531, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Darkomicron", "body": "Loken has several abilities:\r\n[ul]\r\n[li][li]An aura that deals nature damage, to everyone, each second, the further you stand away from him, the more damge you receive.[/li][/li]\r\n[li]A Lightning Nova, that deals around 14k damage on heroic, with nature resistance this damage will be reduced[/li]\r\n[li]A dot that will have a chance to bounce between party members[/li]\r\n[/ul]\r\n\r\nTactics:\r\nTank Loken at the throne, hug the boss, if someone gets the dot, he should stand a bit further away from the boss, he will receive more damage from the aura but the dot wont jump over to other party members.\r\n\r\nWhen he starts casting a nova, everyone should run to the stairs, and immediatly, because you don't have much time from the start of the cast to get out of range.\r\n\r\nKeep going on doing this, you can't LoS the aura or aoe", "date": "2008-12-06T10:38:58-06:00", "rating": 63, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 35, "id": 493761, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "136677", "body": "From playing this morning it seems the big AE did not affect my ghoul pet.  Possible pets do not get targeted by it.", "date": "2008-12-06T12:54:41-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 36, "id": 494196, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "267369", "body": "Ok just did this with a group of Pally tank (me), resto shammy, ret pally, hunter and shadow priest. What we did and made this fight really easy was to put aspect of the wild on (130 nature resist) and just stack on him... Nobody moved and just take in the nova and just heal through it After 3 nova.. he is dead and we even get the achievement :)\r\n\r\nBut maybe what made this really easy was the fact that our shadow priest is aoe healing right after the blast. We just ignored anything else and dps him down.", "date": "2008-12-06T17:24:05-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 37, "id": 494209, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "235419", "body": "Just downed him as a level 77 DK tank (Yes..I tanked it)\n\nEASY fight, barely got me below 60%. Surprisingly dropped TWO of his items too. The necklace and hood. NO DAMN SEAL!. :(\n\nWe just stuck together at his feet and healed through everything. Extremely easy for me.", "date": "2008-12-06T17:27:47-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-12-06T17:29:01-06:00", 1, "235419"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 38, "id": 494278, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "267397", "body": "Confirmed..\r\nthe easiest (best) way not to get wiped is to use the line and move ... staying close all together.\r\nMost important.. After the Nova do not aggro the boss. Just wait for him to come to the tank.\r\nThis way the healer will have the time to do his job...", "date": "2008-12-06T18:06:08-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 39, "id": 494641, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "ninkosen", "body": "This boss when killing someone with his Nova, should yell :\r\n[i]\r\n\"You got stuff, but your skill suxx. Try again and defeat me newbie. Until then burn in hell.\"[/i]\r\n\r\nThis boss reveal skill of people, even good stuffed one, can #$%^ an entire party... I know it, I have been there...", "date": "2008-12-06T22:18:42-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 40, "id": 494655, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "267551", "body": "[b]Heroic[/b]:\r\n\r\nGroup Make-up:\r\n\r\nPaladin (Holy, Healer)\r\nPriest (Shadow, Healer)\r\nWarrior (Protection, Tank)\r\nDeath Knight (Unholy, DPS)\r\nPaladin (Retribution, DPS)\r\n\r\nDeath Knight had T7 (from the 10 man version) leggings and chest. Warrior had T7 (from the 10 man version). Rest of the group was in a various assortment of Heroic and crafted gear.\r\n\r\nOur strategy was simply to eat the Lightning Novas. What we would do, is that I (Holy Paladin) would keep up the tank and myself. The Shadow Priest would heal instead of DPS, and keep the group up. We were unaware of the DoT he put on a group member that spread to others, and we just healed through it. It probably helps that our 2 DPS classes are very high DPS classes, although I believe that even with a bit lower DPS it would work, because of our two healer setup. I strongly reccomend to any group trying this for the first time, or even a group that just can't beat it, to use two healers. We also managed to get the achievement for downing him in less than two minutes.", "date": "2008-12-06T22:31:08-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-12-07T01:01:24-06:00", 1, "267551"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 41, "id": 494891, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Sgtown", "body": "According to Blizzard, Loken is by far the deadliest NPC in Wrath, by a large amount.\r\n\r\n[url=http://www.worldofwarcraft.com/toplist/index.html?en,killedby]Most Dangerous Creatures[/url]", "date": "2008-12-07T01:25:20-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
