{"commentv2": 1, "number": 43, "id": 495540, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "67373", "body": "a trick to make it a bit easier to heal for a holy paladin is to use beacon of light on him/herself and just stay far enough away from loken so its not needed to move when he does his nova", "date": "2008-12-07T10:14:27-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 44, "id": 499155, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "mpmagi", "body": "Possible to use Anti-Magic Zone to get through this \r\n\r\nDPS'ed through Nova by using Anti-Magic Zone on first one. Tranquility on the next. Ran from it on the third Nova.", "date": "2008-12-09T03:03:54-06:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 45, "id": 499390, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "63385", "body": "[b]STACK-N-STAY VERSION[/b] (Heroic Mode)\r\n\r\nWe stayed clumped up in a nice, neat little bunch the entire fight and here is how we killed him:\r\n[ul]\r\n[li]We had a hunter with Aspect of the Wild activated to reduce damage.  Since we were stacked, we only took 800 damage/tick[/li]\r\n[li]Our shaman healer, with +2000 bonus heal, maxed out everyone's health when Loken started to cast his nova. [/li]\r\n[li]Once nova hit, our health was all around 20 - 35%, and healer quickly AoE healed back up.[/li]\r\n[li]We only took 2 novas and finished in under 2 minutes, granting us the  [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?achievement=1867]Timely Death[/url] achievement,[/li]\r\n\r\n[/ul]", "date": "2008-12-09T06:31:56-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 46, "id": 506124, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "275370", "body": "The boss's all do nature damage, and if you have a shaman their nature resistance totem will trivialize this encounter.  I dropped it yesterday on heroic, and the AoE does far less damage, and can easily be healed through.  Provided everyone has the health to absorb the brunt just in case Loken gets lucky. Make sure the moment he starts casting the group is healed to full.\n\nIf you're a shaman don't listen to the melee who think that a haste totem would be better, the nature resistance totem makes this guy a joke.  Just tell them to stand in one spot, and drop the nature resistance totem, have everyone healers included stand in the AE.. it will be weak.\n\nOnce again resists trivialize a heroic boss encounter.", "date": "2008-12-12T15:05:46-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-12-12T15:11:29-06:00", 1, "275370"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 47, "id": 506132, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "275371", "body": "We tried to stay close but that really didnt worked out. We managed to get him somewhere 60% when there were just tank(pala) and healer(priest). From that point on everything went smooth. So just try to get your groub killed. Only tank and healer is needed to take this boss down! Done in heroic.", "date": "2008-12-12T15:10:23-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "haha yes, im a true shaman healer and i must say i had seen this tactic of natur resis totem  (YES THIS GUYS IS A REALLY JOKE SINCE IT)  stay in the same pact with your grp, just be sure that your chain heal will start at the lower health in the grp(like a mage or whatever) he will be instead healed or almost and heal after the guy who got the debuff(lighting something) seriously since this technic, i can really appreciate hall of lightinng becuz this boss who is so hardly for pally is so easy for shammy   so tips for dps and tank(GET A SHAMAN HEALER) IF YOU WANT NO WASTE 3254346546 HRS WITH A", "creationdate": "2008-12-12T15:10:24-06:00", "id": 370423, "rating": 0, "commentid": 506132, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "ruggle", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This fight is blizzard's way of laughing to the faces of all the holy paladins out there.  Don't even bother trying this if you're a healadin.", "creationdate": "2008-12-13T07:48:50-06:00", "id": 370385, "rating": 0, "commentid": 506132, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "129537", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 48, "id": 509999, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "274900", "body": "On Heroic Loken can be tough if you bring the wrong people.  If you bring a decent group he is a joke and goes down like a sack of potatoes but I noticed a huge difference when I just invite anyone who asks...I still do for fun and all...What I noticed it is hard to carry this fight by yourself, but what I do to make it easier (as the tank) is put a raid marker above my head so they know to stay on me and run out.  The camera tip on this thread was also very helpful...to have your camera facing backward while tanking and use the mouse to run out...although trying to explain it to my group was like pulling teeth as they seem to run any direction they want.  \n\nSo anyway, depending on whos in your group you are going to either kill this guy with ease or take a few wipes until they figure it out.  Another thing to do is explain to the healer who is on high priority to get healed if he cannot keep everyone up, that way you have a chance.  Some players may have to be \"let go\" by not receiving heals for the overall success of the fight if they are not playing properly.  I'm talking about rogues who not only do not run out of the nova but also do not use cloak of shadows to eat the nova, instead relying on the healer to pamper them.  Rogues who get hit by the nova yet arent even using sprint give me a good laugh too.  I never booted anyone but I guess if you can identify the problem maybe just replace with a better player, because I've let a lot of things slide and let a lot of players stay even when they refuse to shape up...\n\nAt least they know who is running the show when it is just me and the healer left alive over Loken's dead body...or sometimes just me...mostly because Loken's damage is laughable on Death Knight tanks if you pop the right cooldowns at the right time.  I still just invite anyone for the challenge...cuz I dont need his drops at all...but if I was concerned I'd stack the group with DPS who can keep themselves alive while DPSing.\n\nThat means classes like Warlocks, Shadowpriests, Shamans for the elemental resist totems...I usually have poorly played rogues, hunters, and cat druids so I really gotta step it up....class wouldnt matter too much if people knew how to play their class. Talking about crap like the feral druids who dont even HoT themselves up before they run in but wonder why they go down first...yep...just bring a good crew if you are worried about this guy and he is cake.\n\n I'd say any healer works for this also, even did it with a ret paly healing us (no beacon obviously), mostly about the DPS taking unnecessary damage by not running out or running too far away or running in the entirely wrong direction....walk the line with the group, thats what its for.  Dont run too far, just enough to avoid the nova (range is small IMO).  Lots of people like to blame the healer or the tank but I've noticed a lot of DPSers are just lazy and want to be carried, I mean, you guys do realize some tanks run recount and can see who is carrying their weight.   You know, all you 10% damage done DPS people out there when you should be pulling around 20-30 like the rest of us?  Yeah, I know who you are...seriously...some people need to stop at the AH and buy some upgrades before they try HoL as their first heroic....", "date": "2008-12-14T17:08:24-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-12-14T17:28:20-06:00", 8, "274900"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 49, "id": 512633, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Nycteris", "body": "We did this on normal mode last night. Have the group gather in the small circle in front of him and stack on the tank. We had a hunter in the group who had to stand a bit back to use his ranged attacks - about 5 yards or so. There is no need to run. Just soak the damage and heal through the AOE. Damage is managable. He went down very quickly.", "date": "2008-12-15T20:36:23-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 50, "id": 512706, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "57197", "body": "Nothing hard about it, just need to pay attention to AOE Nova warning!   Lather, Rinse, Repeat\r\n\r\n10 (12-15-2008) Timely DeathDefeat Loken in the Halls of Lightning on Heroic Difficulty in 2 minutes or less.\r\n10 (12-15-2008) Heroic: Halls of LightningDefeat the Halls of Lightning bosses on Heroic Difficulty.\r\n10 (12-15-2008) Shatter ResistantDefeat Volkhan in the Halls of Lightning on Heroic Difficulty without allowing him to shatter more than 4 Brittle Golems.\r\n10 (12-15-2008) Lightning StruckDefeat General Bjarngrim in the Halls of Lightning on Heroic Difficulty while he has a Temporary Electrical Charge.", "date": "2008-12-15T21:31:47-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-12-15T21:33:53-06:00", 1, "57197"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 51, "id": 513596, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "bumba", "body": "I want to emphesize this is an idiot check, not a healer check. The first time i stepped into this instance I was 77 and we one shotted it. \r\n\r\nTho those that have dps who don't follow the strat. Kick them. Its not worth the repair bills.\r\n\r\nIts even recommended that your group take 5 mintues before the fight to read up on it, discuss it, plan your route, and execute.", "date": "2008-12-16T08:40:50-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 52, "id": 513801, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "230695", "body": "Duo'd in normal mode with me as a tank and my fiance on her Pally healing.. she had ~1200 spellpower and roughly ~200 haste rating (enough to make Holy Light 2 second cast) and I had ~22000 HP buffed, just under crit cap(about 520) with about 36% avoidance(Frost Spec DK) my gear was less than perfect.. still is. \n\nHow this came about was.. we engaged the boss with our group.. a mage and a shaman were with us.. I told them to make sure they followed me (in hindsight I should have raidmarked myself) and within the first nova they were both dead. From that point on it was up to me to bring down all 85% of his HP by myself, she stuck on me like glue (for the most part) and ate one nova during it, we finished with her having ~2000 mana and full hp on both parts.\n\nSince then I am crit capped and about 2k more health. Boss is just as simple in heroic.. I doubt we could duo it, or if we could it would be a long fight, even in normal it took us roughly 6 min to single dps him down, and she had to mana pot once.\n\nTips for those of you who have(nt) read ghostcrawlers \"hey noob\" post about how to do this boss:\n\nWhen he starts channeling Nova he has a sort of pulsing radius around him on the ground, this is roughly the range of the nova.. run just a few feet more and you'll be safe (i'd venture to say it's less than 15yd range). I don't recommend moving too much further than that point. \n\nIf you wish to move further to feel like you're out of range then it's your call, I however like to use the ramp and it's nice \"prelit\" line as a guide when I am running, so the less I run the more space I have to kite him before I have to turn and bring him back to the throne. This also saves time for dps to begin on the boss again.\n\n[i]Mark your tank.[/i]  What this does is gives everyone else that can't pay attention or is caught up in the battle a visual to know where to run, they should already know when by the big emote that flashes in the center of the screen. When the emote flashes, follow the {skull} or whatever, wherever he may go. The tanks position is key to this fight because his \"aoe\" damage starts when melee begins (on his part or the tanks); this [i]should[/i] mean when he reaches the tank.\n\nWhy? well because A) you have to get out of range and B) when Loken hits his nova he starts moving toward the tank and if he reaches the tank and starts to attack before you can reach him, you'll start taking aoe damage, this makes it hard on the healer (especially paladins) and most likely in heroic will result in your death.\n\nThat being said there is [i]no[/i] reason to eat the novas. Unless perhaps to go for the achievement if your dps is undergeared and your healer can handle the aoe.", "date": "2008-12-16T10:49:57-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-12-16T10:53:02-06:00", 2, "230695"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 53, "id": 513989, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "MizukoK", "body": "I've seen a few people still asking how to down this boss, so I thought I would post what we usually do in the runs I'm in.\r\n\r\nMy guild members and I usually just do a few things in this fight.\r\nI'm a SV hunter, so I pop my Aspect of the Wild, MD the tank, and it begins. I shoot a few shots as everyone runs in, and then I follow them.\r\nThe tank will take him where he stands, and then Loken will step back twice, right back to his seat. We fight him there.\r\nWe stand on his feet, literally, and dps him down. From time to time I may back out in between the blasts to hit him with a few shots - serpent, explosive etc etc- then I'll run back in and lay an immolation trap. \r\nRepeat, gather badges, gg.\r\nSet up is usually a priest healer, oomkin, pally, (me as the hunter) and a random fifth.\r\nThere's never really a time where we're low enough to be worried, as the healer we have is on top of things, and I feel that my disengage/shoot for a bit/run like hell back to his foot keeps my dps pretty decent.", "date": "2008-12-16T12:41:31-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 54, "id": 515519, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "60999", "body": "90% of the time when I've downed this boss successfully on heroic, even with pugs, we just rely on the healer to keep us up through the nova. As a DK I already don't take hardly any damage from the nova with strategic use of Antimagic Shell, Bone Shield, and Icebound Fort. Between those and deathstrike, the healer can throw a hot on me and focus on other players. Everyone should be using whatever defensive methods they can right at the time the nova hits, to ease the pressure on the healer.\n\nRogues should cloak of shadows. Warrior switch to defense stance. Mages iceblock. Non-tank pallies bubble.  Locks have soulstones and healthstones(and possibly soul link and/or VW to sac). Priests can PW:S and/or heal themselves.  Druids and shamies can also self-heal. \n\nBascially if everyone is on the ball, you let your DPS rip Loken down before he gets off more than about 2 or 3 novas. IMO it's alot simplier and easier to do this way, especially if your healer is well-geared.", "date": "2008-12-17T07:40:20-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-12-17T07:41:24-06:00", 1, "60999"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 55, "id": 518371, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Ryder", "body": "He is the hardest 5-Man Heroic boss and should be nerfed by a simple change , instead of the stupid 4 secs cast make it 5 secs like normal mode.\r\nAll what i can say to those people farming him is either they are TOO overgeared for him or very lucky.", "date": "2008-12-18T18:58:39-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 56, "id": 519917, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "reidsb", "body": "Strangely, we ran this today and it made the group roll for the Stone Keeper Shards, as opposed to having enough for everyone.\r\n\r\nNot sure why.", "date": "2008-12-19T16:33:31-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 57, "id": 520097, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Slythas", "body": "I have another tactic that worked for me and my group (Heroic Mode). We even got the achievement, [li]Timely Death[/li] with this.\n\nMy group consisted of: Combat Rogue (me), Holy Priest, Enhancement Shaman, Fire Mage and  Protection Warrior.\n\nWe hugged each other during the whole fight and nuked the best we could. The priest and Shaman healed through the Nova's. Got him in 1 minute and a few seconds. This was, atleast by our experience, the easiest way of getting him down :)", "date": "2008-12-19T18:49:44-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-12-19T18:52:05-06:00", 3, "Slythas"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 58, "id": 520864, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "130410", "body": "Allegedly the hardest heroic boss, I still think Anub'arak and that first boss in Gundrak are more difficult. This one just requires everyone to pay attention and not watch the dps meters for a change.", "date": "2008-12-20T07:17:42-06:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 59, "id": 522506, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "235419", "body": "Loken. Is. Strong.\r\n\r\nHe hits fairly hard. Has a constant DoT which does more damage the further you are away from him and does an INSANE AoE.\r\n\r\nDefinetly the single hardest boss in all of the heroics of WoTLK. I had people turning me down for PUG's saying they'd rather run it with guildies because it's \"Too hard\"\r\n\r\nManaged to down him with a few randoms just a few minutes ago and it only took us a few wipes.\r\n\r\nI think the most important thing is to keep the tank and healer up. As long as they're alive it can get finished. Albeit a long time, but it'll get done eventually.", "date": "2008-12-21T07:17:23-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 60, "id": 524602, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "286249", "body": "For heroic mode with a holy priest healer:\r\n\r\nGet on vent everyone to explain fight, clear vent during fight\r\n\r\n[u]Tank[/u]:  fight him in the circle the whole time, absorbing the 13k novas every 15(?) sec and 1k pulses every 2 sec.\r\n\r\n[u]Healer[/u]: stand on the step closest to the circle, which is just outside of nova range - don't move - and heal yourself through 3k pulses every 2 sec. As this is a dps race, blow mana with aoe heals after the 1st nova to keep the dps alive long enough to take Loken down.\r\n\r\n[u]DPS[/u]: move and re-position and keep awareness so that you are a) not right next (10yds) to another player ( else 3k arc lightning that jumps), while being b) close enough to Loken when dpsing to take the minimum 1k pulse, but c) not so close to him that you can't move out of range (20yds - not far really) of his nova during its 4 second cast time, while also d) not moving too far out during nova cast, as that will reduce dps and increase pulse damage.", "date": "2008-12-22T11:08:57-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 61, "id": 525315, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "252180", "body": "Does [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=51052]Anti Magic Zone[/url] or [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=48707]Anti Magic Shell[/url] have any effect on his AOE?", "date": "2008-12-22T18:36:54-06:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
