{"commentv2": 1, "number": 63, "id": 526880, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Heckler", "body": "On heroic:  We like to 'wing it' on bosses we've never tried before, Loken's not a great guy to do this on.  Our 3 DPS died in the first 10 seconds, but once me (feral druid) and the healer (resto shaman) got it figured, we 2 manned him the rest of the way down.  Other than it taking a ridiculously long time, it made it clear that the concept of this fight is pretty simple (actually a lot MORE simple with only 2 people involved)...\r\n\r\nStay close to him until he starts to Nova, then get away until its over.  Rinse and repeat.", "date": "2008-12-23T14:20:17-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 64, "id": 527039, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Niroshi", "body": "Something that could help you with running away quick enough if you're melee is just to keep your right mouse button held down, and face your character a little to the side.  You will still be able to hit Loken, Block/Dodge/Parry him (for Tanks) and all you will need to do when you see Lightning Nova is hit your strafe key to get away.\n\nMy groups usually follow the white line down the center of the room and then move back towards his throne whenever you run into the globe, using Lightning Novas as a signal as to when to move him. If you can just avoid his Nova then really you could kill him even with just a Healer and a Tank alive.  Once you get the timing down the fight is remarkably easy.\n\nIf you're a Pally healer and having a hard time with this fight, one of the suggested tactics is to Beacon yourself and stand out of Nova range and just heal everyone up. It worked for my groups until everybody got the above strategy down.", "date": "2008-12-23T16:23:43-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-12-23T18:37:10-06:00", 1, "Niroshi"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 65, "id": 527502, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "288022", "body": "Been farming this instance for a while for the Healing trinket from Ionus. This boss is simplified by just staying in for the AoE Lightning nova. Have your 3 dps and healer stand under the bosses feet and the tank in front of the boss ofc.\r\n\r\nIn terms of healing the novas, use any sort of interrupt protects you can ie. Earth Shield, Concentration Aura, Power Word: Shield even and have your big heal ready to land .1s after the nova. So prayer healing for priest, Wild Growth for Druid, Chain Heal for a Shaman, and Holy Light(with beacon of light on the yourself NOT the tank but heals aimed at the tank) And the boss becomes a doddle. Pop cooldowns when arc lightning makes it difficult to top the group off. If you have stones, use them after the Second Nova as you may have two arc lightings up and keep hots up if at all possible in between big heals.\r\n\r\nEasily healed this the day I dinged 80 with 13.5k hp with a kings as a restoration shaman with a reasonably geared paladin tank.", "date": "2008-12-23T23:16:16-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 66, "id": 527590, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "288077", "body": "The easiest heroic boss in game. Just be sure for everyone to stand on top of him all the fight. His nova hits for ~14k (9k with nature res totem) - easily healed by priest/shammy. Got him down in 50s: tankadin (me) / enh sham / rogue / retadin / holy priest", "date": "2008-12-24T00:48:22-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 67, "id": 532708, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "274900", "body": "Yes, I can stand there tanking novas, in fact I'd say they do trivial damage to me because I have so many ways to reduce magic damage.  Yet I still put the raid marker over my head and teach the group how to avoid them.  Its a matter of skill...I want to see how good my DPSers are sometimes.  When they stand there with their thumb up their butt and go down and it is just me and the healer standing at the end...well, then they know they need to step it up.  If they cant follow me on the light beam given the long cast time window then maybe they deserve to be on the ground. \r\n\r\nEven though he is easy now I still consider him a dangerous heroic boss, because people who hit 80 and are wearing the greens and the blues and never did Loken before are going to be in for a surprise the first time they fight him.  Some groups cant even beat him if they are full of fresh 80s, then they gotta call in Big Papa Kurouzu to show them how its done...been there, done that.", "date": "2008-12-27T11:59:38-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 68, "id": 533301, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "291354", "body": "Did this guy first time today. \r\n\r\nTank asked if I could heal is AOE attack, I said dunno worth a try. \r\n\r\nI was a 79 Restoration shaman, equipped with full Stormhide (LW crafted mail) and some other bits and bobs. \r\n\r\nAt the start of the fight we tried running away. Didn't work too well, whole group took damage, tank obviously took damage and while running I couldn't heal. \r\n\r\nAfter this I decided we stayed put. Kept the chain heals on the go with lesser healing wave for quick top ups. Popped Heroism at around 50%. Very easy. 30% odd mana of 13500 left at end of fight with everyone alive. \r\n\r\nThe elemental boss was harder, popped everything and still ran out of mana and had causalities.", "date": "2008-12-27T19:26:30-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 69, "id": 536342, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "DKRakiel", "body": "Copy/pasting from my comment on overall HoL part:\r\n\r\nKilling Loken in under 2 minutes is quite possibly; its just a DPS check on the fight. \r\n\r\nSuggested Loken Strategy:\r\nIf you notice on the dais that his throne sits on, theirs two bronze bands that run along the length of the stairs. These are going to be your left/right boundary markers. Due to the fact this fight is based on movement I suggest any movement buffs; I particularly like using DK's with Unholy Auras for this factor - just because theres fifty billions DK's and its a passive speed buff that doesn't give you a daze if your hit. \r\n\r\nLoken himself is rather easy - he is fairly squishy; and he doesn't hit that hard - the reason he's such a pain is his abilities can easily ruin your day:\r\n\r\nDoT Aura: The further you are from Loken the more damage you take. So melee ranged targets take the least damage, but if you get far from him you can quite easily end up being one shotted by the aura DoT. \r\nNegating It: The way you have to get around this is rather simple.. Stay close to him; stay in melee range whether or not your melee preferably. Hunters are only really ones that have any issue with melee range and as long as your within the 5 yards it's really all the same anyways.\r\n\r\nArc-Lightning: This is the reverse of the DoT aura; its fundamentally a chain lightning that is really.. Really.. Really evil. You get hit with arc, and anyone near you gets zapped. And than anyone near them gets the arc bounced off them. For pretty nasty damage. Its not so much an issue in normal as it is in heroic, but its a health concern as it will bounce among your group if your all clustered together. However to be fair, with a solid healer and heavy DPS you can simply eat it and therefore not have to worry about positioning. \r\nNegating It: Arc lightning in my opinion is generally the trickiest to negate - the aura you just have to stay close.. The arc lightning you want to try to have 5 yards on each other. What I normally is form a semi-circle on Loken. For a mental image, assume the tank moves Loken to the left boundary marker, and than turns Loken so he's on it and the tanks back is to the right boundary marker. The group than spreads out on the frontal arc of Loken, no-one behind. This makes it so when they have to run, they all run in the same direction and don't have to cross through Loken.\r\n\r\nNova: This is the culmination of all the abilities, and the main reason why people wipe directly - arc lightning might cause big issues or take down someone or two, but Nova will often or not be the closing statement on any wipe. It was stated you can tell when its coming based on the gathering energy at his feet; 5 coils means nova time - but I've never seen this or tried it. Nova simply will eat you alive if you get hit by it - fortunately its easy to avoid. Sort of. \r\nNegating It: Nova is quite easy to escape - it involves Loken standing still and channeling something. However, you have to watch for it and get out of its range. I run on high graphics so I don't know how applicable this is to everyone - but I assume Blizzard puts essential graphics on a \"must render\" setting. If you look at the ground when Loken starts his Nova, you can see the exact radius it has by the boundaries of the crackling lightning and flashing strikes of lightning. Get out of the animation boundaries, your out of Nova. \r\n\r\nTaking Him Down:\r\nLoken is a spank and tank beyond those three abilities. So what you want to do is to grab him and pull him to the aforementioned left boundary marker - the side doesn't really matter, but just stating one for consistency. Once you pull him there, reface him so your back is to the right boundary marker - your group should already be in a loose semi-circle around him. If you get a Arc Lightning bouncing off someone, give them a bit more room. When he starts to channel his Nova, run back to the right side marker. To be honest; you generally only need to run about half way if Lokens on the left marker, but if your having issues on not wiping its better to be safe than sorry.\r\n\r\nOnce Loken finishes his Nova (hopefully sans destroying your group), he will run over to you - reface him so your back is to left boundary and than rinse and repeat. He should die rather easily for you than.\r\n\r\n-Rakiel", "date": "2008-12-29T15:02:22-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 70, "id": 538451, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "293411", "body": "This boss encounter isn't hard at all as long as everyone focus and do their thing. Easiest way to do this by far is simply by:\r\n\r\n1. Start off as a circle around the boss, not standing too close to each other to prevent being hit by the arc lightning.\r\n2. Once the nova starts to cast everyone should move away from the boss. Example: Tank = south, Healer = SE DPS1 = E DPS2 = W DPS3 = SW. The aura is based on distance to Loken, not distance between every team member, meaning which direction you move is irrelevant, as long as you keep at a safe distance to avoid nova + close enough not to get hit too hard by aura.\r\n3. Once nova is cast, everyone move back to the circle in front of his throne, still keeping a safe distance between one another to prevent the Arc Lightning from hitting.\r\n\r\nRepeat this procedure and the boss will be down faster than you can say Loken. Damage is easily avoided in this fight, so the healer will have plenty of mana. Just keep dps steady and stick to the tactics and I guarantee you, he will go down. Used this tactic today and we managed to do it with 3 ppl in early heroic gear.", "date": "2008-12-30T18:22:06-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 71, "id": 540241, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "shadowspa", "body": "ive done all hcs and raids for the champion of the frozen wastes title exept HoL,and all bosses in hc HoL exept loken becouse of his damn retard healer killing spell...oh the horror when the same old cycle repeats:\r\nloken starts casting Lightning Nova\r\nlokens Lightning Nova hits Somerandomhealerguy for 14k\r\nSomerandomhealerguy Dies\r\nSomerandomtankguy dies\r\nSomerandomhealerguy leaves the group\r\nSomerandomtankguy leaves the group\r\nDPS leaves\r\nyour group has been disbanded\r\n\r\nloken is right:I CANNOT RUN FROM FATE wich is that ill probably never get that damn title and COME CLOSER.HE WILL MAKE THE WIPE QUICK so i can start looking for another group", "date": "2008-12-31T19:21:05-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 72, "id": 540930, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Remendador", "body": "Dont run, even in Heroic.\nBring a hunter with Aspect of the Wild and make sure your party is good on dps classes.\nI'm a priest with Lightwell.\nJust make your party use lightwell as soon as Loken begins to cast his aoe so everyone has high amount of HP.\nI begin my Prayer of Healing cast just after Loken begins his cast, so after his hit I can heal everyone fast, than use Circle of healing and always cast prayer of mending.\nIts an easy fight if you do this way.", "date": "2009-01-01T09:12:47-06:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-01-01T09:13:47-06:00", 2, "Remendador"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 73, "id": 541421, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "14493", "body": "here the tactic I am using and so far at a 100% succes rate, at all times stand ontop of the tank and stand still there taking the damage from the AoE, which hit's for about 14.000 damage, and  just outheal it. Do this and you should manage to get the achivement to.\r\n\r\nThis tactic have so far been executed by me as a Druid Healer, just make sure you have HoT's on everyone before the hit and use Wild Growth and Tranquilty. I have also been a part of groups where I was DPS with a Priest healer that started to cast Prayer of Healing before the big hit, also have done it with a Shaman which have Glyphed Chain Heal, he ontop of that used Nature Resistance Totem.", "date": "2009-01-01T15:25:24-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 74, "id": 542167, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "294987", "body": "I did this as a resto shaman, with quite a different strat than mentioned above.\r\n\r\nFirst, Nature resistance is godly here, so keep a nr totem down.\r\nSecond, I had the group not move at all, we just sat on loken the whole time. I could heal through everything spamming chainheals as fast as I could fairly easy.\r\n\r\nIt may be backwards but it worked better than 95% of everything else iv tried on lokan.\r\n\r\nIm fairly geared btw, naxx10-25 level.", "date": "2009-01-02T01:41:41-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 75, "id": 542552, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "146010", "body": "Teach your group to turn and run with the mouse instead of their keyboard. I find that the people who always get caught in it (and inevitably swear they moved) are keyboard turners. Show them the wonders of using the mouse, and let them be enlightened...and often it means they can actually get out of the nova in time the next attempt you make.\r\n\r\nThough I suggest making them practise before you pull, just to be sure. :P (Yes, I'm serious. My sucess rate on loken has gone up since I started doing this.)", "date": "2009-01-02T08:21:33-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Or dps him facing sideways, but ensure that he is still in the forward 180 degrees of your character, and when he starts to channel Lightning Nova, simply strafe to the side.", "creationdate": "2009-01-14T09:50:39-06:00", "id": 72646, "rating": 1, "commentid": 542552, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "178740", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-01-02T08:22:02-06:00", 1, "146010"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 76, "id": 545636, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "275366", "body": "Some guildies just did it without moving.\n\nJust stack on him, and have healer max out everyone's HP before nova goes off, that is if your healer is capable.\n\n\nOur priest did this;\n\nWhen you see AOE coming do [url=\"http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=48072\"]Prayer or Healing[/Url], then do 2 [url=\"http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=34861\"]Circle of Healing[/url]\nAnd use [url=\"http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=48120]Blinding Heal[/url] to keep tank and healer up.", "date": "2009-01-04T01:25:40-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-01-04T01:32:51-06:00", 1, "275366"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 77, "id": 545678, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "withmyrice", "body": "All you rogues: This is yet ANOTHER effect you can CoS through, in case you just HAVE to have that extra 75 dps on your meter at the end of the fight. But I'm sure you all already know that :)", "date": "2009-01-04T02:07:10-06:00", "rating": 6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 78, "id": 548448, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "70634", "body": "[quote]- You want to stay close to him.\r\n- You do not want to stay close to someone else.\r\n- You do not want to be hit by aoe.[/quote]\r\n\r\n^ This is the most important thing to know about the fight.  I had a rough time with it as a Holy Paladin, but once I understood how the right worked we were able to beat it.\r\n\r\nI raid marked the tank, who stood almost inside the boss. Then the remaining 4 people stood in a 4-corner position around the boss, 10 yards apart, but very close to the boss. His aura does more damage the further you are away, and you need to be 10 yards apart to avoid chaining too many Arc Lightnings.\r\n\r\nWhen he starts to cast Lightning Nova, run down the stairs using the white line in the middle of the room as your guide. If you start out tanking him at the very top platform, you should run to the next platform below and STOP at your tank (who is marked), and resume the 4-corner positioning around the boss.\r\n\r\nWhat made the difference to me is explaining this positioning to the DPS so they didn't just go screamingyelling all the way down the stairs, further away from Loken where they start taking increased damage. Once they have their damage controlled, it's really very easy. You can use Holy Shock on the run, or even queue up a Divine Favor + Holy Shock + Instant Flash of Light for the run. Use your cooldowns early in the fight and don't be afraid to Holy Light big damage when it happens.", "date": "2009-01-05T16:02:42-06:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 79, "id": 548974, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "88369", "body": "So yeah.  I just did this on Heroic and the Pally tank wanted us to do it his way.  We would stand at the top of the stairs and he would tank him by the throne.  Needless to say I was VERY skeptical but hey why not.  The raid was full of range, the tank and a pet were the only melee.  Doing it this way kept the party out of Nova.  The Paladin was able to get out of every Nova and reposition him by the throne.  I am a Resto Shaman so I was able to raid heal the group.\r\n\r\nIf you have a range heavy group and have good AoE heals I really recommend this strategy as it almost completely removes the Nova from the equation.", "date": "2009-01-05T23:05:21-06:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
