{"commentv2": 1, "number": 82, "id": 556971, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "301516", "body": "Unfortunately my group has a hard time doing this on normal mostly because they were too slow on running from Lighting Nova not to mention two of them turned with keys to make it worst a dps leaves the group I invited a Death Knight to dps we killed it and my trinket drops(I'm the tank) and so the DK that I just invited needed it, won it, saying that he's going to tank at 80 and after well over two hours of running through the instance and the many wipes that is my reward :P I must have the worst of luck huh?", "date": "2009-01-10T22:35:37-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 83, "id": 561089, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Karoxen", "body": "In the face of his other two abilities, Arc Lightning is trivial. Stacking on top of each other and moving as a group tends to work best regardless of it. \r\n\r\nAlso, Lightning Nova is 20-yard range exactly so certain abilities like shaman shock spells can serve as 'measuring sticks' as to when you get far enough, although going up and down his stairs the natural markers work fine.", "date": "2009-01-13T14:23:46-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 84, "id": 561836, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "xevbe", "body": "Did it yeseterday on heroic with:\n\nProt war\nDPS war\nFeral Druid\nShaman healer\nDemo/Destro lock(me)\n\nWiped a few times because of the movement not working out so on the last try we figuered we all ate the nova. Shaman popped a nature res totem and spammed chain heal... Worked like a charm.\n\nNo one ever came close to dying, shaman had 30% mana left, no bloodlust (used it on try before). Obviously got  the achievement for killing him under 2 min.\nWe all had gear from heroics/naxx.\n\nIf you are geared enough, just stack up at him and dps him down.", "date": "2009-01-14T02:58:03-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-01-14T10:02:56-06:00", 1, "xevbe"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 85, "id": 562144, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "178740", "body": "Easiest way to avoid the nova is to turn on enemy cast bars, or get an addon that displays your target's cast bar somewhere on screen. It's a good idea to have them on in general, but for this fight it's extremely helpful.\r\n\r\nAs a healer, make Loken your focus target and watch his cast bar that way. Everybody else will simply have him targeted at all times. As soon as you see him channel a spell, run! The only spell he casts that has a casting time is Lightning Nova, so you won't confuse it with anything else.\r\n\r\nYou don't need to watch him to do a casting animation, you don't need to watch your chat box for the emote text, you don't need to turn down your spell effects... just look out for a cast bar. Simple!", "date": "2009-01-14T09:48:18-06:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 86, "id": 562340, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "tahini", "body": "Your best bet is to stay in and heal through it.   This works if your healer is good enough.  The running method is even harder to heal, potentially.", "date": "2009-01-14T12:30:23-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
