{"commentv2": 1, "number": 91, "id": 566911, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "119706", "body": "According to what i know of bosses so far, is that Loken is the hardest boss in-game at the moment.\nWith countless whipes behind me, i decided to look more into it.\nThe hardest part is not the AoE, that is easily avoided thanks to Deadly boss mod,\n(or any other addon that shows boss-skill cd's) It's the damn DoT wich makes us whipe!\nHere is what i found out (this goes for HEROIC encounter only!):\n\n[u][b]Lightning nova[/b][/u]\n\n- 20-30 yard range\n- 4 second cast\n- 10-14k Nature damage that can be decreased with totem and normal resistance stats\n\n[u][b]Arc Lightning[/b][/u]\n\n- 50 yard range\n- Jumps to friendly plaYers within 10-20 yards\n- 3-4k nature damage\n\n[u][b]Unnamed aura[/b]\n[/u]\n- infinite range\n- 100 dps per yard (estimated) from loken's target sircle.\n\nSo, when you encounter him, you should stay within his melle target ring.\nHave Deadly boss mod ( http://www.deadlybossmods.com/ ) show you\nthe times between his AoE, start running round 1 sec before he starts his cast.\nNow the hard part.\nRun TOGETHER away from loken, doesn't matter where as long as you get out of AoE's range.\nWhen he has casted it, the tank should STAY at current spot and let loken come to him/her.\nYou will get ONE juicy tick from the aura, but with a healer who can AoE heal, it should do fine.\nEstimated it should only be round 4-5k damage the tick does, depends on range ofc.\nRepeat and you should do fine.\n\nWeird no one has considered DBM here...", "date": "2009-01-17T17:43:07-06:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-01-17T17:43:52-06:00", 1, "119706"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 92, "id": 570441, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Inekadam", "body": "Loken is the best boss i've ever seen.\r\n\r\nHe wears a skirt and sandals and you can get under his skirt.\r\n\r\nNot sure how people kill him despite feeling all that bad smell coming from his foot.", "date": "2009-01-20T03:30:55-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 93, "id": 582321, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "274415", "body": "As posted this fight was a joke on heroic with me (resto shaman) as healer. We didn't run out of the lightning nova once and we got the under 2 min achievement.", "date": "2009-01-26T18:58:15-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 94, "id": 584262, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Skalken", "body": "Just ran tonight with a perfect group.  Here was our strategy.  \r\n\r\nMain tank aggro's Lokken in the circle.  All off tanks attack as well.  Ranged DPS and Healers need to be a couple steps in front of the top step.  This will minimize the ranged dot from Lokken.  \r\nWhen he casts the nova you will see a white pulse on the ground.  You just need to be outside of the white pulse and you won't be hit with the AE.  Main tank needs to not move and take the hit.  \r\n\r\nWe used this strat and main tank never dropped below half and nobody ever lost much health at all.  Almost got the under 2 minutes achievement.  It was 2 min 2 secs...  Next time...\r\n\r\nHope this helps.  \r\nSkalken...", "date": "2009-01-27T22:46:23-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 95, "id": 585262, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "bluephantom", "body": "As decently geared healing priest, it's possible to just have your group stay in for the novas. Have your group topped off before the novas, and time a Prayer of Healing to land right after the nova hits. If there are party members with a low HP pool, however, they may not survive it. I'm not sure about other classes, but if your healer is a confident priest, then this might be a fun way to do it :). He goes down very fast.", "date": "2009-01-28T14:29:52-06:00", "rating": 6, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 96, "id": 592125, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Shuned", "body": "I recommend tanking him in the middle, and when his Nova begins, run left or right not backwards, because you're wasting time spinning around and bolting it, just run the way you're facing, doing this we have never wiped.", "date": "2009-02-02T08:05:51-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Preferably, if you are going to run, run in the same direction. Since he has an aura that does damage based on distance tot he boss it'd be a good idea for the healer to run the same way as everyone else in order to heal the damage.  Otherwise strafing is a pretty good idea. Just do it in a coordinated fashion.", "creationdate": "2009-05-18T05:13:08-05:00", "id": 98619, "rating": 0, "commentid": 592125, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Jinton", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 97, "id": 593786, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "132039", "body": "[quote]We wiped 4 times on this boss on heroic, our healer said the tank had to stay under the boss NO MATTER WHAT, and on top of that, he never ran far enough so he always got one shotted and then he goes and blames it on the tank for DRAGGING TTHE BOSS TOWARDS HIM because our tank was smart and didnt stay under the boss.[/quote]\n\nIf your healer was willing and able to heal your tank through the damage, then it sounds like your healer was right. The tank shouldn't have moved. The healer should have run just far enough to be out of range of the aoe so that the healer wouldn't take excessive damage, and it was the tank's fault for moving Loken.\n\nIf your healer was unable to heal your tank, then it was smart for the tank to move. But even then he should have let the group know he was going to move so the others knew to run farther.\n\nHow can the ranged and healing know how far to run if they don't know what the tank plans to do? If the tank was going to move the boss after someone else said not to, he HAS to tell other people his plans beforehand, or the wipe's his fault.\n\nBased on your description of the situation, and that's all I have to go on, it sounds like the tank was behaving foolishly and the healer was in the right.", "date": "2009-02-03T10:42:56-06:00", "rating": 16, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-02-03T10:43:47-06:00", 1, "132039"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 98, "id": 600169, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "240929", "body": "as a rogue, you don't need to run away if you have a nice healer. just use new feint and cloak of shadows to reduce lightning damage where he is close to cast the lightning nova and keep hitting.", "date": "2009-02-08T05:24:06-06:00", "rating": 6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 99, "id": 600861, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Dauntar", "body": "Fun little thing, if you use a focusing lens on him he will stand up in an angry pose.", "date": "2009-02-08T19:11:18-06:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 100, "id": 601192, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "257676", "body": "As a hunter, you can just pop on aspect of the wild, and the damage done by his AOE and his aura will be minimal, the healer will have a lot easier of time. I am guessing this will work with shaman totems too, but if you have a hunter in your group (or any other class that has nature resist that effects the whole group)this fight can go a lot more smoothly.\r\n\r\nJust an example, when i was fighting him it said something like: -380 (840 resisted)", "date": "2009-02-09T01:12:20-06:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 101, "id": 603331, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "lizbliz", "body": "Finally, a fight where Apsect of the Wild actually came in handy. We whiped 3 times against his guy and on the 4th times I actually remember I had that dam aspect (the last time I used it was in Maraudon, seriously) and we took so much less damage as a group it wasn't even funny.\r\n\r\n(I plan on running HoS for the pants that drop off of the boss and I looked him up to find he did mostly natural damage as well. Looks like Aspect of the Wild is a good idea for both of these bosses if you are having issues with too much damage happening to the party as whole.)\r\n\r\nI can haz 130 nat resist ftw please?", "date": "2009-02-10T15:48:26-06:00", "rating": 11, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 102, "id": 606210, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "321871", "body": "Just finished this boss for the second time on heroic so here\u00b4s my 2 cents on Loken:\r\n\r\nEveryone just hug him, stand real close to each other. Even on AoE, just stand there, as long as you got a decent/good healer it\u00b4s definitely easier to stand around him and \"hug\" him. Don\u00b4t split up your group because you\u00b4ll take one hell of alot more damage from his aura if you step away from the others.\r\n\r\nOur groupsetup was a DK unholy tank, a blood DK, combat rogue, affliction warlock and holy paladin(me). Last time I was there we tried to run from the nova with lil\u00b4 to no success, we got separated and well, at least I died, and in that wiping the whole group. That being said I was badly geared back then.\r\n\r\nThis time however we just hugged Loken, I simply put up Beacon of Light on the tank and spamhealed everyone after the AoE. Having the Glyph of Holy Light helps seeing how you heal every groupmember within five yards of the healing-target whenever you cast Holy Light. Having the Glyph of Flash of Light also helps seeing how you crit more with your 1.5 sec cast spell. And of course; Holy Shock.\r\n\r\nWe even got the achievement, so as long as everyone got more than 14000 hitpoints (our lock just had 15000) I\u00b4d say the hug-strategy is a lot easier and time efficient than the run back and forth strategy.", "date": "2009-02-12T11:30:21-06:00", "rating": 9, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 103, "id": 607666, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "deustele", "body": "Did this last night as a pally healer. We went for the timed kill and did it in 51 seconds. Using a ranged dps group, everyone stacked on me at the top of the stair's. Beacon the tank and let him start the fight, tanking him on the base of the throne, focus on using HL spam on the stacked group, while having the tank soak the nova, The bouncing aoe is at best a joke and the aura is steady damage to everyone allowing HL glyph to shine. All in all a very smooth and quick kill.", "date": "2009-02-13T11:05:35-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 104, "id": 611202, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "TheNocturnal", "body": "This is my first post on WOWhead and I just really had to post this after reading so many peoples tactics on trying to fight LOKEN.... honestly when you all read this and try it , you are gonna laugh at how easy LOKEN is....\r\n\r\nso dont worry about running from his AOE\r\nhis DOT ...pshh is no big deal...\r\nALL YOU HAVE TO DO IS HAVE THE WHOLE GROUP STAND BETWEEN HIS LEGS! the whole group is never hit by the AOE if standing directly in the middle of his legs right under LOKEN.... then you can just TANK and SPANK all to hell !\r\n\r\nAnd I actually had never knew this or tested it til Heroic Mode...which it worked 100% even in Heroic.... So for everyone out for the Skull-Clad Cleaver... Never fear anymore when you run this...for everytime will be just as easy as the last.\r\n\r\nHOPE THIS HELPS! ENJOY! ---- Lesnar - [Horde] Deathknight Tank from sever Muradin", "date": "2009-02-16T01:47:40-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 105, "id": 620791, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Mojazu", "body": "Just did Loken for the first time on Heroic as holy priest.\r\nIt was a piece of cake. We even got the Timely Death achievement.\r\nWe basically just hugged the boss the entire time even on the nova. I was quick to aoe heal the group back to full health after nova with Prayer of Healing (+Prayer of Healing glyph). I started to cast in the middle of his Nova spell so the heal would land right after damage taken so the small dot wouldent becomne a problem\r\nIt was important to keep everyone topped off right before Nova or they would have died.\r\n\r\nThis strategy requires everyone to have at least 19k+ health. With less health the nova would probably have become pretty deadly\r\n\r\nGroup was:\r\nPriest(Healer)\r\nDruid(tank)\r\nMage\r\nRogue\r\nDeath Knight", "date": "2009-02-23T15:39:40-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "pw:s is that needs to be said", "creationdate": "2009-03-13T19:01:56-05:00", "id": 393859, "rating": 0, "commentid": 620791, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "150236", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 106, "id": 632404, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "332875", "body": "I had to comment because I found a way that was easier than anything I read about here.  We had tank/healer pallies and 3 warlocks, on heroic.  All we had to do was this:\r\n\r\nStart in a close group facing the same way.  When he starts to cast, everyone just walk backward!  That is all!  Then stop backing up when he's done!\r\n\r\nNo AoE damage, hardly any damage at all, healer did very little healing.  It was sooooo simple.  No turning to run, nothing.  Just hit the backarrow key.  Got the fast kill achievement as well.", "date": "2009-03-05T16:25:31-06:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 107, "id": 640516, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "336033", "body": "Thought I would throw my two cents in. I tanked this for the first time the other night and took two tries, the first time we did the run from his nova spell and that did not work. The second we stacked and it worked very well and this is how we did it. \r\n\r\nFirst off I am a unholy Dk Tank and this is a very good fight for unholy dk tanking specs. You should Tank him right under were his is sitting in the white circle area.  When he cast nova the first time just drop your anti-magic shell and it will keep the group from taking much dmg at all the first round of the nova and the heals will have an easy time dealing with that. The second time he cast nova the healer should have the whole party as close to topped off as possible and the dk tank uses his personal anti magic shield and takes basically no dmg so the healer can focus on himself and the rest of the party( and at this point I think its more important to make sure heals keeps themself alive than the other dps) . After this point its just matter of the tank mitigating dmg and the healer doing the best he can to heal himself and the tank and remaining dps to kill Loken as fast as possible. If your party understands that there is a good chance they will die on this boss(the dps) then there should not be a big problem. When we did this only the rouge died and he was under geared for the dungeon.\r\n\r\nTank- Unholy Dk\r\nHeals- Druid\r\nDps- Dk\r\nDps- Rouge\r\nDps- Hunter", "date": "2009-03-12T22:01:06-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 108, "id": 644548, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "337557", "body": "I personally think it's a shame, that one of the \"greater\" northern gods, is listed as one of theese low level dungeon bosses... (In level 80 means.)\r\nI mean, so much northern lore is based upon him - so why drop him in such a low position?\r\nAnyhow, no time to moan.\r\nAlthough he crushed me with his lighting last time, I still find him silly...", "date": "2009-03-16T15:34:55-05:00", "rating": 9, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I completely agree. For all the story behind Loken he deserved more than to be the boss of a dungeon.  He was named the supreme protector of Azeroth by the Pantheon and after his betrayal he was in control of Ulduar. http://www.wowwiki.com/Loken  I really think he should have been the second to last boss of Ulduar.  Although having him as the boss of Halls of Lighting made it possible to get a satisfying conclusion to the major story arc of Storm Peaks.", "creationdate": "2009-12-04T20:27:50-06:00", "id": 135384, "rating": 2, "commentid": 644548, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Maxtro", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Loke was hardly an official part of the northern pantheon. Oh, he was quite important, but he was kinds of outside the pantheon. He was also never really particularly good at fighting, unlike Thor (duh), because he was a manipulator. Loken is actually incredibly unlike Loke in all regards.", "creationdate": "2012-03-23T11:05:00-05:00", "id": 529843, "rating": 0, "commentid": 644548, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Arikara", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 109, "id": 651677, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Eugee", "body": "Found a new way to heal this guy as a Holy Paladin:\r\n\r\nTank keeps him in one spot (we did left pillar).\r\nHealer stands outside Nova range, with Beacon of Light on themselves.\r\nDPS stand at max melee a little spread out for arc-lightning.\r\n\r\nAs Loken casts Nova the tank soaks it while the DPS range it.  The healer will time a Holy Light right after it lands.  Very easy to range the nova like this and the tank and healer stay healthy.  Beacon more than counters the damage from being at range.", "date": "2009-03-22T13:36:43-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I don't know if this has been mentioned before, but if you have a hunter in the party, just have him put up Aspect of the Wild. With 130 Nature resist, neither of his AoE attacks (proximity or nova) did damage. The only damage we took was from the lightning debuff bouncing between the party members. It was ridiculously easy.", "creationdate": "2009-03-27T22:05:28-05:00", "id": 88004, "rating": 1, "commentid": 651677, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "234212", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 110, "id": 653139, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Jinton", "body": "[quote]As a norse guy[...][/quote]\r\n\r\nI can 100% guarantee that you are in fact not norse. From a nordic country, Scandinavian, Norwegian, maybe. Norse - no. The vikings were norsemen. The era of vikings ended about 1000 ad.\r\n\r\n[quote][i]Norse [/i]and [i]Norsemen[/i],are applied to the Scandinavian population of the period from the late 8th century to the 11th century.[small]\r\nQuoute from Wikipedia: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Norsemen[/small][/quote]\r\n\r\nAnd for all of you debating and arguing about specifics in mythology: [u]It is a waste of time.[/u]\r\n\r\nThe stories are, like the biblical stories, mouth-to-mouth recollections of tales invented thousands of years ago, long before vikings.They were told and retold in endless variations changing from one person to the next and altering each time it was told. That Snorre Sturlasson wrote some of those variations down does not make his Edda the one correct version.\r\n\r\nTL DR: Your version is NOT [u]the[/u] correct version - ever.", "date": "2009-03-23T17:35:12-05:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
