{"commentv2": 1, "number": 112, "id": 660597, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "182762", "body": "Incredibly easy on heroic. \r\nMy group (Retadin, Holy Priest, Prot Warrior (me), Demon Lock, and a Frost DK)\r\nWe got the achievement on the first try. We stayed in for his lightning blasts. He's not that hard. Get everyone over 17k health, and it's super easy", "date": "2009-03-30T14:34:19-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 113, "id": 661195, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "134628", "body": "Shaman healers want to have everyone stack on the boss and stay there, not moving.\n[b]Drop nature resist totem[/b] and keep riptide ticking on the person with the lowest HP. Cast chain heal right after nova starts on that person, so it hits right after. Then 2-3 CHs through the tank, and repeat.\n\nThis greatly increases DPS and makes the fight so much simpler for you.\n\nPeople will end up taking Much less damage, as the aura will be doing next to nothing.\nIf you think about it, ~10k dmg isn't a lot to heal through, especially when you know it is coming.\n\nKeep a NSed CH ready if things get bad, but the fight only takes around a minute thirty, so you will have Heroism / BL up half of the fight. \n\nI have done this with 3 pugs and 1 shotted each time.", "date": "2009-03-31T04:02:52-05:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-03-31T04:09:36-05:00", 1, "134628"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 114, "id": 667774, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "yzerman", "body": "Just ran this 4 times in a row and finally got the strategy down. \r\n\r\nThere are 3 levels to the platform he is on, tank him on the middle platform facing away from where the tank wants the group to run. The trick to this tactic is to have everyone stack close to Loken (melee range). Where most groups fail is the next part of the tactic:\r\n\r\nWhen the raid warning shows - everyone run to the bottom of the stairs to the lower platform. Once everyone gets to the bottom of the platform turn and run back as quick as possible. The trick is not to outrun Lightning Nova, but to run as far away as nova will reach (~30 yards) and get back as quickly as possible before the Lightning debuff procs, as on Normal it hits for about 5k at 30 yards, Lightning Nova hits for about 4k at melee range. Melee range the lightning debuff is almost unnoticable to most people. To make my point, the last run we 4 manned this fight with a 80 DK tank, 80 Shammy heals, 78 DK melee DPS and an 80 Warlock, and noone came close to dying.", "date": "2009-04-06T13:48:38-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 115, "id": 667921, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "293302", "body": "If you learn to avoid his AoE, he is extremely easy.\r\n\r\nI have 2-manned him as Holy Pala + Prot Pala.", "date": "2009-04-06T16:44:16-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-04-06T17:02:41-05:00", 1, "293302"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 116, "id": 670126, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "ricekrispieslol", "body": "i think he looks bored.........dont all bosses? i mean they just sit there and wait to be killed...................i know id want to fight if i had to just sit there", "date": "2009-04-08T18:11:56-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 117, "id": 672623, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "71095", "body": "I have done Halls of Lightning more than 20 times and I can say that Loken is the easiest boss ever if you have a Shaman in your group, either healer or DPS. The tactic I use is very simple:\r\n\r\n- All people should stay near each other, hug the boss during the whole fight, and NOT run away when Loken does his AOE.\r\n- The Shaman should put Nature Resistance Totem and begins to cast Chain Heal while Loken is casting his AOE. 2-3 Chain Heals and all people will be at full health again.\r\n\r\nYou can use this tactic with both Restoration and DPS Shamans. If the Shaman is DPS, just tell him to stop DPSing and spam 2-3 Chain Heal to help the healer. Add Bloodlust and Fire Elemental Totem (if available) and you will easily get [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?achievement=1867]this[/url] at first try.\r\n\r\nAll people used to fear Loken and consider it one of the hardest Heroic bosses, but I can guarantee that this tactic makes him the easiest boss ever. Killed him more than 20 times and never wiped, even with bad groups.", "date": "2009-04-11T04:39:02-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 118, "id": 674619, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "236163", "body": "Bit of trivia:\r\n\r\nThe voice of  Loken was done by [url=http://joeactor.com/]Joe T. Thomas[/url].\r\n\r\nHe also voiced Krik'thir the Gatewatcher and the Death Knight's ghoul pet.", "date": "2009-04-13T01:38:08-05:00", "rating": 13, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 119, "id": 675084, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "PinkWolf", "body": "there's an [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=3582#same-model-as]Aman[/url] in wetlands that looks exactly like Loken...odd", "date": "2009-04-13T11:03:35-05:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 120, "id": 708590, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Pipolla", "body": "As a Holy Paladin, this fight can be rather hard keeping everyone up. After many wipes i suggested this strategy, resulting in a clean easy kill:\r\n\r\n[ul]The group should hug the boss apart from the Paladin, who should stand just over 20 yards away, to find out if you're far enough away, try casting Holy Shock on Loken. If you can't you're in position.\r\n[li]The Paladin should keep Beacon of Light on himself throughout the fight, this mitigates the increased damge taken from Loken's pulsing aura.\r\n[/li] When Loken starts to cast Lightning Nova, the Paladin won't have to move meaning he can continue healing whilst everyone else runs out; if possible your tank should take the hit and continue tanking him; this requires less group coordination and makes this fight a cakewalk.\r\n[/ul]\r\n\r\nI hope this helps any Paladins/Groups having trouble with this encounter.", "date": "2009-05-07T12:36:21-05:00", "rating": 10, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 121, "id": 709990, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "316283", "body": "Was the range of the nova changed recently?\r\n I remember the nova only being like 20 yards long and it was more than enough time to run away, even with a bad ping and keyboard turning ...\r\nbut now I can't make it anymore not even with strafing IMMEDIATELY", "date": "2009-05-08T19:49:07-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 122, "id": 710852, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "363545", "body": "hey so i was running this about a week ago and something weird happened. Everytime he did lightning nova, none of us would move and the Aoe wouldnt effect anyone. I dont know if this was a glitch or what? but it was the easiest fight i have ever done. Give me some feedback on to what you guys know about this, thanks.", "date": "2009-05-09T15:50:16-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 123, "id": 727513, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "318094", "body": "This fight is absurdly easy to heal through for a priest on Heroic.\r\n\r\nThe first time I came here, I tried the ranged tactic I did on normal to little success. Even if you escape the Lightning Nova, the periodic AoE effect will eat you alive and you cannot properly heal your group if you're constantly worried about yourself. After two wipes, we tried a different tactic. Hug that sucka, which seems to be the preferred approach in the comments regardless.\r\n\r\nThis fight is where Holy Nova SHINES, Discipline OR Holy, and I'm Holy. Everyone stands as close as possible, right under him if you can. The tank tries not to move too much so people don't gain distance from him. The priest spams Holy Nova ALL the time, except for when Circle of Healing and/or Prayer of Mending are off cooldown. Critical heals and damage save lives here (Disc will continually proc Divine Aegis; Holy will continually proc Surge of Llight, which guarantees a free heal to one party member or a free Smite to Loken).\r\n\r\nWhen you get the message that he's casting Lightning Nova, you shield yourself, and time a Prayer of Healing or Divine Hymn to hit right after the blast. Then you get back to the HN spam. If you run out of mana, target Loken and pop your fiend, who will not have much to worry about AoE-wise so you'll get a lot of mana back.\r\n\r\nThere is no priest you can have except for one with weak healing that won't be able to heal through this AND get the Timely Death achievement for you.\r\n\r\nSome observations I've made: Druids and Shamans should be able to heal through this without worry because of their nature resist buffs and/or totems. Holy Pallies should be able to heal through this by systematically healing with Holy Light (glyphed) to keep everyone up. They should probably continually shift the target of their beacon so that they're always healing two people at a time for a lot while everyone else benefits from the little heal that the glyph provides (which should be significant because of Holy Light crits). If someone's life is too low to survive a Nova, I suspect that Divine Intervention will keep them up and they can immediately join the fray after the blast. It really isn't complicated regardless of the healer involved.\r\n\r\nI will say this: Hunters, even if you have to occasionally abandon your shooting range to avoid taking huge damage, it's more prudent to keep as close as possible and maybe just let your pet do the fighting, step out to fire a quick ability, then hop right back in. I think Hunters have the hardest time with Loken because in order to do their dps, they've gotta stand farther away which hurts them more in the long run. After my first time running H HoL with a hunter in our group and seeing him get ripped to shreds from the AoE after a Nova, I give hunters that very warning. Stay close even if you have to abandon your dps to do it.\r\n\r\nBut yeah. This is the definition of tank n' spank otherwise. At least as long as I'm healing for ya.", "date": "2009-05-25T18:45:18-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "a dead hunter does 0 dps", "creationdate": "2009-10-27T17:42:28-05:00", "id": 129467, "rating": 4, "commentid": 727513, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "358623", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 124, "id": 738114, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "364466", "body": "This boss is pretty hard, but having a shaman, priest, or a druid healer can make it easyer. Remember to run away when he uses his nova, on heroic my group wiped 2 times because most people didn't move away", "date": "2009-06-05T14:12:17-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 125, "id": 747818, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "mathos22", "body": "To confirm Kronus was his original name, after you kill him, check your recount (if you have it). As of 6/15/09, recount still registers Loken as \"Kronus\".", "date": "2009-06-15T17:03:03-05:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 126, "id": 750634, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "272357", "body": "I'm just gonna repeat what [b]fieryshadowcard [/b]said and that is that as a priest Loken was veery easy with holy nova spamming.\r\n\r\nWe tried Loken scattered all over the place first trying to avoid the nova. Wipe. Alt + tab and read his/hers reply about holy nova (had forgotten all about it) and next try we gather at his legs and I spam HN and he went down very fast (got the ach).\r\n\r\nI did it as a disc priest.", "date": "2009-06-18T16:52:42-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Loken's last words after he is defeated, \"My death... heralds the end of this world\", is not an empty threat. Loken was Azeroth's prime designate tasked to watch over and protect the planet, as well as act as a guard of the imprisoned [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=33288]Yogg-Saron[/url]. It was Loken's death that triggered the failsafe device that caused [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=32871]Algalon the Observer[/url] to be dispatched to Azeroth to investigate, and, if needed, re-organize all of Azeroth, which meant destroying it so it could be rebuild from it's remains.  You can see the h", "creationdate": "2009-06-18T16:52:43-05:00", "id": 412395, "rating": 8, "commentid": 750634, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 6408, "username": "CalaelenDT", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 127, "id": 767417, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "418201", "body": "For everyone saying that tanks drag the boss towards the party when using the AoE: Loken doesn't move period when casting it and in fact helps the party because he runs towards them after casting it, reducing the aura damage. And I've found that tanking him from pillar to pillar to be extremely easy, no real distance judgment calls besides getting to the pillar on the other side.", "date": "2009-07-04T08:24:03-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-07-04T08:25:15-05:00", 1, "418201"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 128, "id": 773030, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "409787", "body": "Loken was once a noble keeper within the titan city of ulduar, but recently the old god Yogg-Saron has taped into the minds of Ulduar's greatest guardians in attempt to release himself from the prison he was trapped in many years ago. Loken had succumbed to the beast's will and gone insane along with other guardians. Loken had taken the wife of his dear brother Thorim causing Thorim much anger.\r\n\r\nIn one quest within the storm peaks Thorim challenges his brother Loken, but thorim was defeated and taken back to ulduar where he had fallen under Yogg-Saron's grasp.", "date": "2009-07-09T17:02:14-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 129, "id": 774665, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "tobindax", "body": "I hope wowhead had most important comments on the top, and not the earliest - and more clueless.\n\nTHIS IS NOT ONLY ABOUT RUNNING FROM NOVA.\n\nIT'S ALSO ABOUT STAYING TOGETHER.\n\nIT AOES MORE IF YOU ARE FAR APART.\n\nI wish this was on top comment.\n\n\nALMOST ALL pugs I join think it's only about running away, so we have 2 or 3 wipes before I CONVINCE THEM WITH CAPITALS (yes, sometimes it's the only way) that you don't just have to run in 7 directions, but to hug one person, usually the tank.\n\n\n\n\nThat, or aoe heal it with an imba healer stationary (not able to half of the time).", "date": "2009-07-11T10:02:38-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-07-11T10:04:43-05:00", 1, "tobindax"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 130, "id": 787773, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "368256", "body": "easiest way to do this boss if everyone has more than 14k HP is to just stand on him and let him hit everyone with nova (using nature totem hunter aura etc as needed) and heal through it...only disc preists should have trouble healing this (due to a slightly less abundant choice of AoE heals) but still a cakewalk ^_^", "date": "2009-07-24T22:03:55-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 131, "id": 792550, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Modibybob", "body": "Strategy as a resto shaman.\n\nEveryone else piles up under him as normal, drop healing stream totem and nature resist toem. This mitigates much damage from the aura.  The shaman stays a tad farther away than everyone else and here is why.\nThe very second he begins casting nova, run out of range and start casting chain heal.\nIf timed right, the chain heal will hit everyone immediately after the nova. Chainheal again if you need to, and riptide/lesser yourself for the aura damage and go back in.  Repeat as needed.", "date": "2009-07-29T21:11:57-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-07-30T01:11:44-05:00", 1, "Modibybob"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 132, "id": 792574, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "288048", "body": "This fight isn't really as hard as the other comments take it to be. (might've been nerfed in 3.1)\r\n\r\n I just finished this fight on heroic with me (a blood tank), and a Ret paladin healing me due to the fact that our first charge at him the nova 1 shotted our healer and 2 dps leaving me and the pali for 75% of the fight. \r\n\r\nThis may not work so well for other tanking classes but if you hug the boss even on heroic the damage he pulls out is laughable to the point that the ret palli was keeping both of us up with little trouble considering he was in ret greens and blues. (little trouble given those circumstances is still kinda painful)\r\n\r\n the only huge issue was the nova which I just shelled the first and fourth, sacced my ghoul for the second  and used vamp. blood along with my health tap for the third. the paladin had about 20k health so he just focused on healing himself when the nova hit us both.\r\n\r\n When you do this fight just pay attention to your health, the AoE damage is huge but between 2 characters the fight really isn't to hard.\r\n\r\nI bet this could be done with a prot palli fixing himself up after the nova as well if he lost his healer like me. (this is assuming a dps can off heal a little bit)\r\n\r\nFunny thing about our run was the pali was barely breaking 500 dps and was looking to be useless until that final fight.", "date": "2009-07-29T21:43:23-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 133, "id": 793076, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "124872", "body": "If you're having problems healing everyone at the same time, try padding everyone up ! Just have the party buff up on Nature Resistance...\r\nBring a [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=49071]hunter[/url] or a [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=58749]shaman[/url], even just a [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=48470]druid[/url] might work, have the party get some [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=44939]Lesser Flask[/url]s[url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=44939] of Resistance[/url] and even [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=40216]Mighty Nature Protection Potion[/url]s, and this boss will be a walk in the park. It worked wonders against [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=23574]Akil'zon[/url], it works wonders here too (and against most other bosses with AoE damage).\r\nLoken seems to have little to no Spell Penetration. Just from a hunter's aura or a shaman's totem, I resist 10 to 25% of the damage from each of his [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=59835]Nova[/url]s, and [b]over 50%[/b] of that of his Pulsing Shockwave ! Which makes the [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?achievement=1867]Achievement[/url] all that more reachable. Note that http://www.wowwiki.com/Resistance really doesn't talk about AoE spells, at the Blizzard link they have in the References, it was specified that the table was for [i]Direct Damage[/i] spells.\r\nNR is especially helpful against [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=52921]Arc Lightning[/url], too: the more NR individual party members have, the better the chance on each leap that it will be resisted and stop spreading !\r\nSure, NR is optional if the whole group is alert enough to be able to get out of the Novas correctly. But if you know you have difficulties with that, then stack up on NR, and you'll be able to afford staying at a distance despite his permanent AoE hurting more (or somewhere in between, where running away from the Nova is a lot easier; or as others have suggested, just soak up the Novas). Maybe even wear one or two NR greens from the Auction House, you'll lose some stats, but you lose even more dps or healing power when you croak ;)  Plus relieving strain from the healer seems to be crucial, here.\r\nSo try it before knocking it (or at least before downrating this post), you'll be surprised... Players stack up on Resilience for the Arenas. Do you really think Blizzard put Magic Resistance in the game for no reason ?", "date": "2009-07-30T11:10:31-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-08-05T11:24:31-05:00", 10, "124872"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 134, "id": 793786, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "434436", "body": "I have found this easiest healing as a holy paladin.\r\n\r\nTank should tank him somewhere in the middle, and dps and heals stack on him too help with the AOE, when Nova begins to cast, all DPS run, begin casting holy light on yourself, so when the nova is cast, you get the heal and it is beaconed off to the tank, cast holy light and holy shock on any DPS who may of got hit and top everyone off ready for the next nova.", "date": "2009-07-31T05:13:18-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
