{"commentv2": 1, "number": 137, "id": 829619, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "54671", "body": "Once you have the gear to survive the lightning nova with about 10-15% of your health, definitely stay grouped for the nova.\r\n\r\nJust got him down in 44 seconds on heroic, so that's definitely the way to do it.. stay in tight, don't move, and just burn him down.. If you have any sort of bubble or shield, throw it up so it's on when Nova hits, but otherwise, don't worry about it.\r\n\r\nThe last boss of Heroic HoS has a much more nasty lightning nova then this guy does.", "date": "2009-09-02T01:55:25-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 138, "id": 835190, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "jGarand", "body": "With the overall gear level changes for casual players in 3.2, even the most average geared DPS has enough HP to survive his nova, the common strategy seems to be to just ignore the Nova and burn him. \r\n\r\nLast i was in a group (as a healer) he only managed to cast once, dying midcast his second.", "date": "2009-09-08T08:45:25-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 139, "id": 840606, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "jaq1010", "body": "Easy fight on both modes now. Heck I just did a run helping some lower geared people on normal and we beat him with only myself (Level 80 Blood DK geared for Trial of the Crusader) and a lower geared Pally tank, and a brand new 80 Druid healing. Loken's a piece of cake with the amount of gear you can get now.", "date": "2009-09-15T03:18:00-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 140, "id": 858029, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "312797", "body": "Successfully soloed as a protection paladin. My group died on the first nova. What I did was threw up seal of light and divine plea and just judged light. When he'd do his nova I'd run out and heal myself. Easy enough to desperately solo once you have the gear.", "date": "2009-10-02T21:36:04-05:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 141, "id": 876742, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "358623", "body": "lol i did this to but i  purposly did the run to see if it was possible.\nfirst i ran thru the place naked dying quite a bit.\nthen i put on my a T-8 25 man gear (blood DK). threw up Mark of blood with frost presence. whenever loken started to cast the nova i just used AMS. death strike and blood tap? (whatever its called, heals for 20%  max health) kept me above 50 % the whole time. took about 5 mins to do. used one potion, AotD, and ghoul and IBF", "date": "2009-10-27T16:37:22-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-10-27T16:38:02-05:00", 1, "358623"]}
