{"commentv2": 1, "number": 0, "id": 478772, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Jaxis", "body": "Thinking maybe this is a reference to the Warhammer Horus Heresy character Garviel Loken, seems to fit the profile of the astartes.", "date": "2008-11-29T19:04:46-06:00", "rating": -5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Try Norse mythology. Loki, trickster 'god' who helped the Aesir gods only so long as it fit his whims, more often than not caused them plenty of grief, and ultimately betrayed the other gods and fought against them in Ragnarok. Highly simplified, of course, but that is the general gist.", "creationdate": "2008-12-02T12:10:11-06:00", "id": 61254, "rating": 18, "commentid": 478772, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "775", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 1, "id": 495977, "nreplies": 7, "sticky": 0, "user": "Khane", "body": "Loki'n/Loken/Loke is the panther lightning god of Norse mythology, he follows around Argual and defeats him in ragnorak, as such, his brother, Thorim is born. Thorim and Loken are originally allies and defeat Jormungand, the serpent god, (this how the name for the jormungar serpents was born), but were split. Now Thorim is good and Loken is evil due to the chaotic energy of the twisted yggdrassil.", "date": "2008-12-07T14:51:10-06:00", "rating": -5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "This is so painfully incorrect it nearly hurts to read. At best I think you perhaps got your mythologies mixed up, especially since there are no panthers in Scandinavia, the historic homeland of the Norsemen. In fact, there are no large cats known to live in the northern reaches of Europe concurrent with human civilization.  Loki was blood brothers with Odin, as mentioned below, and part or wholly giant in descent, depending on the source. And in one of the more ... moments in mythology, he was the [i]mother[/i] of Odin's eight-legged horse Sleipnir. He is fated to fight Heimdall, keeper of th", "creationdate": "2008-12-07T14:51:11-06:00", "id": 369751, "rating": 15, "commentid": 495977, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "775", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Oh yes... The Aesir had hired an outside craftsman to build a huge wall around Asgard, but due to his boasts of capability they told him that he must finish it in seven days, or be damned to Hel.  He came close to accomplishing this, due to his unnaturally strong horse, but then Loki hatched a plan: He changed his shape to that of a mare, and led the craftsman's horse astray. Unable to finish the wall without his horse, he was damned to Hel.  Loki, still in the form of a mare, later gave birth to Sleipnir from the 'episode' with the craftsman's horse. If I remember correctly, his horse was tak", "creationdate": "2008-12-07T14:51:11-06:00", "id": 369908, "rating": 5, "commentid": 495977, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Thrakin", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "sleipnir was taken by Odin to ride.", "creationdate": "2008-12-30T03:48:07-06:00", "id": 68716, "rating": 2, "commentid": 495977, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "292862", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I meant the craftsman's horse, but yes, Sleipnir was taken as a mount by Odin. It also has a 'cameo' [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=8280]here[/url].", "creationdate": "2009-01-10T01:34:36-06:00", "id": 71635, "rating": 2, "commentid": 495977, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Thrakin", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "He is obviously trolling   i mean i stopped at panther lightning god lol.", "creationdate": "2009-06-23T20:33:10-05:00", "id": 412325, "rating": 0, "commentid": 495977, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Firebrandt", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 2, "id": 501645, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Thrakin", "body": "Don't know where you read that, Khane...\r\n\r\nLoki is the blood brother of Odin, the god of war in the Norse pantheon. He is occasionally depicted as being 'within' the Aesir, but in Ragnarok he will fight one of the aesir ( Can't remember which one ). He is the father of Fenris, Jormungandr ( World Serpent ) and Hel, the goddess of the underworld.", "date": "2008-12-10T08:41:45-06:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 3, "id": 511361, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "254037", "body": "Nice chit-chat about Loken and gods but nowhere in this commentlist is ANY information how to kill him =/", "date": "2008-12-15T09:02:38-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "This should not be downrated. Its would be helpful to many people who use wowhead.", "creationdate": "2008-12-16T15:12:50-06:00", "id": 371604, "rating": 0, "commentid": 511361, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "DoomHammer", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Just did him on normal. Pretty easy fight. He casts an AE blast, when he starts casting you run out. Then run back in. Stay close because the further you are from him, the more his aura ticks you for.", "creationdate": "2008-12-17T21:28:41-06:00", "id": 372114, "rating": 0, "commentid": 511361, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "atomhead", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Go, then, to [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=28923]this page[/url] which is Loken's appearance in the Halls of Lightning. This entry on Loken is the unattackable NPC who shows up at the culmination of Thorim's storyline to avenge the past betrayals by Loken.", "creationdate": "2008-12-18T12:20:19-06:00", "id": 65807, "rating": 3, "commentid": 511361, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "775", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
